'''Dua Lipa''' ({{IPAc-en|ˈ|d|uː|ə|_|ˈ|l|iː|p|ə|audio=En-us-Dua-Lipa.ogg}} {{respell|DOO|ə|_|LEE|pə}}, {{IPA|sq|ˈdua ˈlipa|lang}}; born 22 August 1995)<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Bowenbank |first=Starr |date=23 August 2023 |title=Dua Lipa Takes Fans Inside Birthday Dinner With Boyfriend Romain Gavras |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/dua-lipa-birthday-dinner-boyfriend-romain-gavras-1235399438/ |access-date=14 March 2024 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US |archive-date=14 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240314165352/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/dua-lipa-birthday-dinner-boyfriend-romain-gavras-1235399438/ |url-status=live }}</ref> is an English and Albanian{{Efn|Born in London to [[Kosovo Albanian]] parents, Lipa obtained [[Albanian citizenship]] in 2022.}}<!-- See MOS:CONTEXTBIO and talk page discussion before changing. --> singer and songwriter.<!--DO NOT ADD NON-NOTABLE JOB, SEE [[MOS:ROLEBIO]].--> Her voice and [[disco]]-influenced production have received critical acclaim. [[List of awards and nominations received by Dua Lipa|Her accolades]] include seven [[Brit Awards]] and three [[Grammy Awards]]. ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' magazine included her in [[Time 100|its list]] of the top 100 most influential people in the world for 2024.<ref>{{Cite magazine |date=15 April 2024 |title=Dua Lipa Manifested All of This |url=https://time.com/6965325/dua-lipa-interview-time100-2024/ |access-date=16 April 2024 |magazine=TIME |language=en |archive-date=16 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240416162548/https://time.com/6965325/dua-lipa-interview-time100-2024/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

Lipa worked as a model before signing a recording contract with [[Warner Records|Warner Bros.]] in 2014. She rose to prominence with her [[Dua Lipa (album)|eponymous debut album]] in 2017, which peaked at number three on the [[UK Albums Chart]] and spawned the singles "[[Be the One (Dua Lipa song)|Be the One]]", "[[IDGAF (Dua Lipa song)|IDGAF]]", and the UK number-one single "[[New Rules]]". Lipa was honoured with the Brit Awards for [[Brit Award for British Female Solo Artist|British Female Solo Artist]] and [[Brit Award for Best New Artist|British Breakthrough Act]]. Her second single, "[[One Kiss (song)|One Kiss]]" with [[Calvin Harris]], was the [[List of best-selling singles by year in the United Kingdom|best-selling song of 2018 in the UK]] and won the [[Brit Award for Song of the Year]]. In 2019, she won the [[Grammy Award for Best New Artist]] and for [[Grammy Award for Best Dance/Electronic Recording|Best Dance Recording]] for "[[Electricity (Silk City and Dua Lipa song)|Electricity]]", her collaborative single with [[Silk City (duo)|Silk City]].

Lipa's second album, ''[[Future Nostalgia]]'' (2020), became her first UK number-one album, and won the [[Brit Award for British Album of the Year]] and the [[Grammy Award for Best Pop Vocal Album]]. Its lead single, "[[Don't Start Now]]", scored the [[List of songs which have spent the most weeks on the UK Singles Chart|longest top-ten stay]] for a British female artist on the [[UK Singles Chart]] and ranked in the top five of the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] [[Billboard Year-End Hot 100 singles of 2020|year-end chart of 2020]]. The album's success continued with the follow-up singles "[[Physical (Dua Lipa song)|Physical]]", "[[Break My Heart (Dua Lipa song)|Break My Heart]]", and "[[Levitating (song)|Levitating]]", the last of which topped the [[Billboard Year-End Hot 100 singles of 2021|''Billboard'' year-end Hot 100 chart of 2021]] and was certified [[RIAA certification|diamond]] in the US. Lipa subsequently scored her third and fourth UK number-one singles with the 2021 [[Elton John]] duet "[[Cold Heart (Pnau remix)]]" and "[[Dance the Night]]" from the [[Barbie the Album|soundtrack]] of the film ''[[Barbie (film)|Barbie]]'' (2023), wherein she also made her acting debut. In 2024, she released her third studio album, ''[[Radical Optimism]]'', which debuted atop the [[UK Albums Chart]] and was preceded by the UK top-ten singles "[[Houdini (Dua Lipa song)|Houdini]]", "[[Training Season]]", and "[[Illusion (song)|Illusion]]". She also had a supporting role in the [[spy film]] ''[[Argylle]]''. Lipa, as one of the wealthiest people in the UK, was included in the ''[[Sunday Times Rich List]]'' for 2024, with an estimated net worth of £90 million.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Watts |first=Robert |last2=Goss |first2=Alexandra |date=2024-05-17 |title=Dua Lipa net worth{{snd}}Sunday Times Rich List 2024 |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/dua-lipa-net-worth-sunday-times-rich-list-xxtf2dlrj |url-access=subscription |work=[[The Times]] |language=en |issn=0140-0460}}</ref>

==Early life==
Lipa was born in [[London]],<ref name="allmusicbio">{{cite web|last=Yeung|first=Neil Z.|title=Dua Lipa {{!}} Biography & History|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/dua-lipa-mn0003426731/biography|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210325004824/https://www.allmusic.com/artist/dua-lipa-mn0003426731/biography|archive-date=25 March 2021|access-date=24 March 2021|publisher=[[AllMusic]]}}</ref> the eldest child of [[Kosovo Albanians|Kosovo Albanian]] parents Anesa ({{Nee|Rexha}}) and Dukagjin Lipa from [[Pristina]], [[FR Yugoslavia]] (present-day [[Kosovo]]).<ref name="press kit">{{Cite web|title=Global Press Kit|url=https://press.warnerrecords.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/dua-lipa-global-press-kit_1481573911262.pdf|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200709101300/https://press.warnerrecords.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/dua-lipa-global-press-kit_1481573911262.pdf|archive-date=9 July 2020|access-date=15 February 2021|website=[[Warner Records]]}}</ref><ref name="bbc">{{cite web|last=Savage|first=Mark|date=9 February 2016|title=Dua Lipa: A pop star in waiting|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-35520865|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160210092743/https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-35520865|archive-date=10 February 2016|access-date=7 May 2016 |work=[[BBC News]]}}</ref> Her maternal grandmother is of [[Bosniaks|Bosniak]] descent.<ref name="talecities" /><ref>{{Cite web|last=Butler|first=Will|date=15 April 2018|title=Dua Lipa speaks on Brexit, Trump and her family history in new interview|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-brexit-trump-family-history-new-interview-2293339|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180419190958/https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-brexit-trump-family-history-new-interview-2293339|archive-date=19 April 2018|access-date=25 April 2021|website=NME|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="fun">{{Cite web|last=Lamont|first=Tom|date=15 April 2018|title=Dua Lipa: 'Pop has to be fun. You can't get upset about every little thing'|url=http://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/apr/15/dua-lipa-pop-has-to-be-fun-you-cant-get-upset-about-every-little-thing-new-rules|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180415122433/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/apr/15/dua-lipa-pop-has-to-be-fun-you-cant-get-upset-about-every-little-thing-new-rules|archive-date=15 April 2018|access-date=25 April 2021|website=The Guardian|url-status=live}}</ref>

Her ancestry can also be traced back to the city of [[Peja]], Kosovo. Both of her grandfathers were historians.<ref>{{Cite web|url= https://rtv21.tv/vajzat-pejane-ambasadoret-e-kosoves/|title=Peja's ambassadors|website=rtv21|date=15 April 2017|access-date=27 April 2021|archive-date=28 April 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210428233223/https://rtv21.tv/vajzat-pejane-ambasadoret-e-kosoves/|url-status=dead}}</ref> She has a sister named Rina and a brother named Gjin.<ref name="guardian2">{{Cite web|last=Snapes|first=Laura|date=3 April 2020|title=Dua Lipa: 'You have to be made of steel to not let words get to you'|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2020/apr/03/dua-lipa-you-have-to-be-made-of-steel-to-not-let-words-get-to-you|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200403051224/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2020/apr/03/dua-lipa-you-have-to-be-made-of-steel-to-not-let-words-get-to-you|archive-date=3 April 2020|access-date=20 January 2021|website=[[The Guardian]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.capitalfm.com/artists/dua-lipa/family-mum-dad-siblings-brother-sister/|title= Dua Lipa's Family: From Her Mum Anesa & Dad Dukagjin To Her Siblings|website=Capital FM|date= 25 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220102113205/https://www.capitalfm.com/artists/dua-lipa/family-mum-dad-siblings-brother-sister/|archive-date=2 January 2022|access-date=26 November 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="telegrafi">{{Cite web|last=Bajraktari|first=Behare|date=20 January 2011|title='Era' dhe 'ODA': Rikthim, sukses, pasion!|url=https://telegrafi.com/era-dhe-oda-rikthim-sukses-pasion/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160812123552/https://telegrafi.com/era-dhe-oda-rikthim-sukses-pasion/|archive-date=12 August 2016|access-date=10 January 2021|website=[[Telegrafi]]|language=Albanian}}</ref> Lipa was musically influenced by her father,<ref name="nylon">{{Cite web|last=Gore|first=Sydney|date=23 October 2015|title=Band Crush: Dua Lipa|url=https://www.nylon.com/articles/dua-lipa-interview|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151025001133/https://www.nylon.com/articles/dua-lipa-interview=|archive-date=25 October 2015|access-date=11 January 2021|website=[[Nylon (magazine)|Nylon]]}}</ref><ref name="digitalspy" /><ref name="hungertv">{{Cite web|last=Fraser|first=Holly|date=26 October 2016|title=Dua Lipa On Falling in Love With Music and Growing Up Fast|url=https://www.hungertv.com/feature/dua-lipa-on-falling-in-love-with-music-and-growing-up-fast/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161031022553/https://www.hungertv.com/feature/dua-lipa-on-falling-in-love-with-music-and-growing-up-fast/|archive-date=31 October 2016|access-date=10 January 2021|publisher=Hunger TV}}</ref> who was the lead singer and guitarist of the Kosovan rock band Oda.<ref name="abcnews">{{Cite web|last=Soichet|first=Aude|date=10 October 2018|title=How Dua Lipa went from aspiring singer to one of today's top global female pop stars|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/dua-lipa-aspiring-singer-todays-top-global-female/story?id=58393549|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181011015440/https://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/dua-lipa-aspiring-singer-todays-top-global-female/story?id=58393549|archive-date=11 October 2018|access-date=10 January 2021|website=[[ABC News]]}}</ref><ref name="observer" /><ref name="telegrafi" /> Her father continued to play music at home, including his own compositions and songs of artists such as [[David Bowie]], [[Bob Dylan]], [[Radiohead]], [[Sting (musician)|Sting]], [[The Police]], and [[Stereophonics]].<ref name="digitalspy">{{Cite web|last=Davidson|first=Amy|date=11 December 2015|title=Meet your new favourite popstar Dua Lipa – just don't call her the new Lana Del Rey|url=https://www.digitalspy.com/music/new-music/a776876/meet-your-new-favourite-popstar-dua-lipa-just-dont-call-her-the-new-lana-del-rey/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190319180711/https://www.digitalspy.com/music/new-music/a776876/meet-your-new-favourite-popstar-dua-lipa-just-dont-call-her-the-new-lana-del-rey/|archive-date=19 March 2019|access-date=11 January 2021|website=[[Digital Spy]]}}</ref><ref name="hungertv"/><ref name="clash">{{Cite web|last=Martin|first=Felicity|date=3 February 2017|title=The Realest It Gets: Dua Lipa|url=https://www.clashmusic.com/features/the-realest-it-gets-dua-lipa|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170203205350/https://www.clashmusic.com/features/the-realest-it-gets-dua-lipa|archive-date=3 February 2017|access-date=10 January 2021|website=[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]]}}</ref> Dua Lipa began singing at the age of five.<ref name="thecut">{{Cite web|last=Peoples|first=Lindsay|date=27 April 2017|title=Dua Lipa Is the Anti–Pop Star|url=https://www.thecut.com/2017/04/dua-lipa-singer-interview.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170926095353/https://www.thecut.com/2017/04/dua-lipa-singer-interview.html|archive-date=26 September 2017|access-date=11 January 2021|website=[[New York (magazine)#The Cut|The Cut]]}}</ref>

Lipa grew up in [[West Hampstead]], London.<ref name="observer">{{Cite web|last=Walker|first=Shaun|date=5 August 2018|title=Dua Lipa's father stages music festival for 'peace-loving' Kosovo|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/aug/05/dua-lipa-father-organises-kosovo-music-festival|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180805123539/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/aug/05/dua-lipa-father-organises-kosovo-music-festival|archive-date=5 August 2018|access-date=10 January 2021|website=[[The Observer]]}}</ref> She attended [[Fitzjohn's Primary School]]<ref>{{Cite web|last=Chapman|first=Helen|date=30 November 2017|title=Dua Lipa's former school plays New Rules to pupils each morning|url=http://camdennewjournal.com/article/dua-lipas-former-school-plays-new-rules-to-pupils-each-morning|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613112046/http://camdennewjournal.com/article/dua-lipas-former-school-plays-new-rules-to-pupils-each-morning|archive-date=13 June 2018|access-date=14 January 2021|website=[[Camden New Journal]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=5 December 2017|title=Londoner's Diary: How Shulman is filling the void left by Vogue|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/londoners-diary/londoner-s-diary-how-shulman-is-filling-the-void-left-by-vogue-a3710761.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210114220932/https://www.standard.co.uk/news/londoners-diary/londoner-s-diary-how-shulman-is-filling-the-void-left-by-vogue-a3710761.html|archive-date=14 January 2021|access-date=14 January 2021|website=[[Evening Standard]]}}</ref> and her music lessons there included the cello.<ref name="bbc"/> When she auditioned to enter the [[Choir#In schools|school choir]], the teacher told her that "she could not sing".<ref name="bbc" /><ref name="digitalspy" /><ref name="nytimes">{{Cite web|last=Pareles|first=Jon|date=31 May 2017|title=Dua Lipa Was Raised on Pop Bangers. Now She Writes Them.|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/05/31/arts/music/dua-lipa-interview.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170721203734/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/05/31/arts/music/dua-lipa-interview.html?_r=0|archive-date=21 July 2017|access-date=11 January 2021|website=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref> At the age of nine, she began weekend singing lessons at the [[Sylvia Young Theatre School]].<ref name="bbc"/><ref name="talecities">{{Cite web|last=Nash|first=Ed|date=8 November 2016|title=A Tale of Two Cities|url=https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/features/longread/a-tale-of-two-cities|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170731192954/https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/features/longread/a-tale-of-two-cities|archive-date=31 July 2017|access-date=10 January 2021|website=[[The Line of Best Fit]]}}</ref><ref name="elle">{{Cite web|last=Levy|first=Lauren|date=9 April 2019|title=Dua Lipa Is the Future of Pop Music|url=https://www.elle.com/culture/a27075435/dua-lipa-grammy-interview/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190411190139/https://www.elle.com/culture/a27075435/dua-lipa-grammy-interview/|archive-date=11 April 2019|access-date=12 January 2021|website=[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]}}</ref> Lipa moved with her family to Pristina after [[2008 Kosovo declaration of independence|Kosovo declared independence]] in 2008.<ref name="talecities"/><ref name="thecut"/> There she attended Mileniumi i Tretë School,<ref>{{Cite web|date=17 March 2016|title=Në cilën shkollë shkoi Dua Lipa në Prishtinë (Foto)|url=https://telegrafi.com/ne-cilen-shkolle-shkoi-dua-lipa-ne-prishtine-foto/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160320112106/https://telegrafi.com/ne-cilen-shkolle-shkoi-dua-lipa-ne-prishtine-foto/|archive-date=20 March 2016|access-date=11 December 2021|website=[[Telegrafi]]|language=sq|url-status=live}}</ref> learned more about the [[Albanian language]], and considered a music career.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Collins|first=Simon|date=29 May 2017|title=From Kosovo to the world, Dua Lipa is on the rise|url=https://thewest.com.au/entertainment/from-kosovo-to-the-world-dua-lipa-is-on-the-rise-ng-b88487005z|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170731195933/https://thewest.com.au/entertainment/from-kosovo-to-the-world-dua-lipa-is-on-the-rise-ng-b88487005z|archive-date=31 July 2017|access-date=12 January 2021|website=[[The West Australian]]}}</ref><ref name="eveningstandard2">{{Cite web|last=Godwin|first=Richard|date=1 November 2017|title=Dua Lipa: meet pop's hottest property|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/lifestyle/esmagazine/dua-lipa-meet-pop-s-hottest-property-a3672811.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201221171738/https://www.standard.co.uk/lifestyle/esmagazine/dua-lipa-meet-pop-s-hottest-property-a3672811.html|archive-date=21 December 2020|access-date=13 January 2021|website=Evening Standard}}</ref>

At age 15, Lipa moved alone back to London and shared a flat with a family friend.<ref name=":0">{{Citation |title=The Graham Norton Show – Series 31: Episode 19 |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/iplayer/episode/m001wlh0/the-graham-norton-show-series-31-episode-19 |access-date=24 February 2024 |language=en-GB |archive-date=24 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240224012225/https://www.bbc.co.uk/iplayer/episode/m001wlh0/the-graham-norton-show-series-31-episode-19 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="rollingstone">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-cover-story-1113124/|title=Dua Lipa: Dancing in the Dark|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|last=Morris|first=Alex|date=14 January 2021|access-date=14 January 2021|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210114140842/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-cover-story-1113124/|archive-date=14 January 2021}}</ref><ref name="eveningstandard">{{Cite web|last=Smyth|first=David|date=29 July 2016|title=Dua Lipa talks about her teen years in Kosovo and why it's tough for new music artists to break through|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/culture/music/dua-lipa-talks-about-her-teen-years-in-kosovo-and-why-it-s-tough-for-new-music-artists-to-break-through-a3307341.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210112043247/https://www.standard.co.uk/culture/music/dua-lipa-talks-about-her-teen-years-in-kosovo-and-why-it-s-tough-for-new-music-artists-to-break-through-a3307341.html|archive-date=12 January 2021|access-date=12 January 2021|website=Evening Standard}}</ref><ref name="Norton2024" /> At [[Parliament Hill School]] she passed her [[GCE Advanced Level (United Kingdom)|A-Levels]], then re-entered Sylvia Young Theatre School part-time.<ref name="eveningstandard"/><ref name="harper">{{cite magazine|last=Gonzales|first=Erica|date=31 January 2017|title=Dua Lipa Recovered from a Rough Modeling Career to Become a Pop Sensation|url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/culture/art-books-music/news/a20019/dua-lipa-interview/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202083436/https://www.harpersbazaar.com/culture/art-books-music/news/a20019/dua-lipa-interview/|archive-date=2 February 2017|access-date=18 January 2021|magazine=[[Harper's Bazaar]]}}</ref> She uploaded her own songs to [[SoundCloud]] and [[YouTube]]. She began posting videos of herself covering songs such as "[[If I Ain't Got You]]" (2004) by [[Alicia Keys]] and "[[Beautiful (Christina Aguilera song)|Beautiful]]" (2002) by [[Christina Aguilera]] on YouTube.<ref name="thecut"/> Lipa modeled with [[Topshop]]<ref name="rollingstone"/> and signed with a modeling agency, helping her land a role as a "singer" in an [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] advertisement for ''[[The X Factor (British TV series)|The X Factor]]'' in 2013, covering the song "[[Lost in Music]]" (1979).<ref>{{cite web|last=Murphy|first=Lauren|date=30 August 2017|title=Watch: Turns out Dua Lipa appeared on an ad for The X Factor back in 2013|url=https://entertainment.ie/music/watch-turns-out-dua-lipa-appeared-on-an-ad-for-the-x-factor-back-in-2013-253465/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190320191217/https://entertainment.ie/music/watch-turns-out-dua-lipa-appeared-on-an-ad-for-the-x-factor-back-in-2013-253465/|archive-date=20 March 2019|access-date=13 January 2021|website=|publisher=[[entertainment.ie]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Cragg|first=Michael|date=26 March 2020|title=Dua Lipa – 'Future Nostalgia' review|url=https://crackmagazine.net/article/album-reviews/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200326235126/https://crackmagazine.net/article/album-reviews/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia/|archive-date=26 March 2020|access-date=4 March 2021|website=[[Crack Magazine]]}}</ref> She acquired a producer and a manager.<ref name="press kit"/><ref name="eveningstandard"/>

==Career==
===2013–2018: Career beginnings and ''Dua Lipa''===
[[File:British singer and songwriter Dua Lipa at the SWR3 New Pop Festival 2016.jpg|thumb|right|Lipa in 2016|262x262px]]
In 2013, Lipa signed a contract with Tap Management, directed by Ben Mawson and Ed Millett, while working as a waitress in a cocktail bar. Lipa was introduced to Mawson by her lawyer, who discouraged her from signing another publishing deal that was offered to her. They then offered her a monthly salary to leave her job and focus on recording music.<ref name="mbw">{{cite web |url=https://www.musicbusinessworldwide.com/artists-have-the-best-chance-of-success-when-they-get-things-rolling-themselves/ |title=Artists have the best chance of success when they get things rolling themselves. |date=22 June 2018 |work=Music Business Worldwide |first=Rhian |last=Jones |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200730091708/https://www.musicbusinessworldwide.com/artists-have-the-best-chance-of-success-when-they-get-things-rolling-themselves/ |archive-date=30 July 2020 |access-date=18 January 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> During one of the sessions Lipa co-wrote the song "[[Hotter than Hell (Dua Lipa song)|Hotter than Hell]]",<ref name="mbw" /> which led to her signing a record deal with [[Warner Records|Warner Bros. Records]] in 2014.<ref>{{Cite web|date=18 August 2017|title=Breakthrough Artist Dua Lipa Lands First Number One Single in UK & Ireland with 'New Rules'|url=https://www.wmg.com/news/breakthrough-artist-dua-lipa-lands-first-number-one-single-uk-ireland-new-rules-27631|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170826120451/https://www.wmg.com/news/breakthrough-artist-dua-lipa-lands-first-number-one-single-uk-ireland-new-rules-27631|archive-date=26 August 2017|access-date=18 February 2021|website=[[Warner Music Group]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Paine|first=Andre|date=23 July 2018|title=New ruler: Dua Lipa's debut album goes platinum|url=https://www.musicweek.com/talent/read/new-ruler-dua-lipa-s-debut-album-goes-platinum/073269|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181029152247/https://www.musicweek.com/talent/read/new-ruler-dua-lipa-s-debut-album-goes-platinum/073269|archive-date=29 October 2018|access-date=18 February 2021|website=[[Music Week]]}}</ref> Millett retrospectively elaborated: "Dua was really smart–she signed to Warner Bros. partly because they didn't have a big female pop artist and they needed one. They really wanted her, so she had the focus of the team from day one."<ref name="mbw" />

In August 2015, Lipa released her [[lead single|first single]], "[[New Love]]",<ref name="pj0815">{{cite web|url=http://www.popjustice.com/briefing/meet-dua-lipa-a-very-good-new-singer/137908/|title=Lana Del Rey's management have a new artist and she is amazing|date=21 August 2015|work=[[Popjustice]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150822132651/http://www.popjustice.com/briefing/meet-dua-lipa-a-very-good-new-singer/137908/|archive-date=22 August 2015|url-status=live|access-date=10 June 2019}}</ref> produced by [[Emile Haynie]] and [[Andrew Wyatt]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Weber|first=Lindsey|date=9 December 2015|title=Meet Dua Lipa, a Restless Spirit with a Mighty Big Voice|url=https://www.thefader.com/2015/12/09/dua-lipa-gen-f-interview |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151212234902/https://www.thefader.com/2015/12/09/dua-lipa-gen-f-interview |archive-date=12 December 2015|access-date=12 January 2021|website=[[The Fader]]}}</ref> Her second single, "[[Be the One (Dua Lipa song)|Be the One]]", was issued to European success in October 2015,<ref name="guardian-shake">{{cite web |last=Lester |first=Paul |author-link=Paul Lester |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2016/jan/01/shake-it-up-future-female-stars-2016 |title=Shake it up: the future female pop stars of 2016 |work=The Guardian |date=1 January 2016 |access-date=7 May 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160102114204/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2016/jan/01/shake-it-up-future-female-stars-2016 |archive-date=2 January 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="guardian1015">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/musicblog/2015/nov/09/the-playlist-new-bands-with-the-prettiots-dua-lipa-and-mind-enterprises|title=The playlist: new bands – with the Prettiots, Dua Lipa and Mind Enterprises|last=Lester|first=Paul|date=9 November 2015|work=The Guardian|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151111055921/https://www.theguardian.com/music/musicblog/2015/nov/09/the-playlist-new-bands-with-the-prettiots-dua-lipa-and-mind-enterprises|archive-date=11 November 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> reaching number one in Belgium,<ref name="BEL">{{cite web|url=https://www.ultratop.be/nl/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Dua+Lipa|title=Discografie Dua Lipa|publisher=[[Ultratop]]|language=nl|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160828214130/https://www.ultratop.be/nl/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Dua+Lipa|archive-date=28 August 2016|access-date=3 May 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Poland and Slovakia, as well as charting in the top ten in over eleven European territories. In Australia and New Zealand, the song became an airplay success, reaching numbers 6 and 20 respectively.<ref name="AUS">Peaks in Australia:
*All except noted: {{cite web|url=https://australian-charts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Dua+Lipa|title=Discography Dua Lipa|website=australian-charts.com|access-date=3 May 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160805194837/https://australian-charts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Dua+Lipa|archive-date=5 August 2016|url-status=live}}
*"Blow Your Mind (Mwah)": {{cite web|url=http://www.noise11.com/news/australian-singles-the-chainsmokers-and-halsey-spend-seven-weeks-at-no-1-20160926|title=Australian Singles: The Chainsmokers and Halsey Spend Seven Weeks At No 1|last=Ryan|first=Gavin|date=26 September 2016|publisher=Noise11|access-date=26 September 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160926154424/http://www.noise11.com/news/australian-singles-the-chainsmokers-and-halsey-spend-seven-weeks-at-no-1-20160926|archive-date=26 September 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> In November 2015, she was revealed as one of the acts to appear on the [[BBC]] [[Sound of...]] 2016 long list.<ref name="bbc1215">{{cite web |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03br1k6 |title='I want to work with A$AP Rocky' – Dua Lipa talks dark pop and hip hop influences |publisher=[[BBC Radio 1]] |date=10 December 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160323184327/http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03br1k6 |archive-date=23 March 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref>

{{Quote box|width=20em|quote=We've seen artists who might get half a good song out of 10 writing sessions; with Dua, one in five or one in four is a banger. She gets results out of other people as well, because her personality is so engaging and she is so charismatic. She definitely has that special something.|source=—Ben Mawson on Lipa's songwriting<ref name="mbw" />}}

Her first tour in the UK and Europe began in January 2016,<ref name="digitalspy" /> and concluded in early December 2016.<ref name="livenation">{{Cite web|url=http://www.livenation.co.uk/artist/dua-lipa-tickets|title=Dua Lipa Tickets|date=13 May 2016|work=Livenation|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161116194033/http://www.livenation.co.uk/artist/dua-lipa-tickets|archive-date=16 November 2016|url-status=live|access-date=14 May 2016}}</ref> On 18 February 2016, Lipa released her third single, "[[Last Dance (Dua Lipa song)|Last Dance]]", followed by "Hotter than Hell" on 6 May. The latter was successful particularly in the UK, where it peaked at number 15.<ref name="UK">{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/48638/dua-lipa/|title=Dua Lipa|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|access-date=14 May 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171119070618/http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/48638/dua-lipa/|archive-date=19 November 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> On 26 August, her fifth overall single, "[[Blow Your Mind (Mwah)]]", was released, peaking at number 30 in the UK.<ref name="UK" /> It became the singer's first entry on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], debuting at number 72.<ref name="US">{{cite magazine|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=Dua Lipa|chart=Hot 100}}|title=Dua Lipa – Chart history: Hot 100|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=26 October 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220930060903/https://www.billboard.com/artist/dua-lipa/chart-history/hot-100/|archive-date=30 September 2022|url-status=live}}</ref> The song also topped the [[Dance Club Songs|''Billboard'' Dance Club Songs]] chart<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/artist/6752366/Dua+Lipa/chart?f=359|title=Dua Lipa – Dance Club Songs {{!}} Billboard|magazine=Billboard|access-date=5 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170102082343/https://www.billboard.com/artist/6752366/Dua+Lipa/chart?f=359|archive-date=2 January 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> and reached number 23 on the [[Mainstream Top 40|''Billboard'' Mainstream Top 40]] chart.<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/artist/6752366/Dua+Lipa/chart?f=381|title=Dua Lipa – Mainstream Top 40 {{!}} Billboard|magazine=Billboard|access-date=5 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170102175956/https://www.billboard.com/artist/6752366/Dua+Lipa/chart?f=381|archive-date=2 January 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>

Lipa was featured on [[Sean Paul]]'s single "[[No Lie (Sean Paul song)|No Lie]]", released in November 2016,<ref name="NoLie">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/7648036/sean-paul-dua-lipa-no-lie-video|title=Watch Sean Paul Get Reflective With Dua Lipa in 'No Lie' Video: Exclusive|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Bein|first=Kat|date=10 January 2017|access-date=27 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202100330/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/7648036/sean-paul-dua-lipa-no-lie-video|archive-date=2 February 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> which reached number ten in the UK.<ref name=":1">{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/charts/singles-chart/20170203/7501/|title=Official Singles Chart Top 100 {{!}} 3 February 2017 – 9 February 2017|publisher=Official Charts Company|access-date=4 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170214071222/http://www.officialcharts.com/charts/singles-chart/20170203/7501/|archive-date=14 February 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> The song became a top-ten hit in ten countries six years after its release, and it became Sean Paul's most-streamed song as of December 2022. The music video (directed by [[Tim Nackashi]]) surpassed 1 billion views on YouTube in April 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://urbanislandz.com/2022/04/21/sean-paul-dua-lipas-no-lie-surpasses-1-billion-views-on-youtube/|title=Sean Paul, Dua Lipa's "No Lie" Surpasses 1 Billion Views On YouTube|work=Urban Islandz|last=Leslie|first=Soje|date=21 April 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220516114302/https://urbanislandz.com/2022/04/21/sean-paul-dua-lipas-no-lie-surpasses-1-billion-views-on-youtube/|archive-date=16 May 2022|access-date=22 April 2022|url-status=live}}</ref> The following month, a documentary about Lipa named ''See in Blue'' was commissioned by ''[[The Fader]]'' magazine.<ref name="See in Blue">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zxZPR4jxOM4|title=Dua Lipa – See in Blue (Documentary)|work=The Fader|via=[[YouTube]]|date=20 December 2016|access-date=5 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170112050311/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zxZPR4jxOM4|archive-date=12 January 2017|url-status=bot: unknown}}</ref> In January 2017, Lipa won the [[European Border Breakers Award|EBBA]] Public Choice Award,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.musicweek.com/talent/read/dua-lipa-scoops-public-choice-award-at-the-ebbas/067121|title=Dua Lipa scoops Public Choice Award at the EBBAs|last=Legrand|first=Emmanuel|date=12 January 2017|access-date=13 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612142014/http://www.musicweek.com/talent/read/dua-lipa-scoops-public-choice-award-at-the-ebbas/067121|archive-date=12 June 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> and released the single "[[Scared to Be Lonely]]", a collaboration with [[Martin Garrix]], reaching number 14 in the UK.<ref name="Scared">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/7669858/martin-garrix-dua-lipa-scared-to-be-lonely|title=Martin Garrix and Dua Lipa Drop New 'Scared to Be Lonely' Video: Watch|magazine=Billboard|date=27 January 2017|access-date=27 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202102245/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/7669858/martin-garrix-dua-lipa-scared-to-be-lonely|archive-date=2 February 2017|url-status=dead|last=Bein|first=Kat}}</ref>

In May 2017, she performed at the anniversary of Indonesian television channel [[SCTV (Indonesia)|SCTV]] and won the award for Young and Promising International Artist at the [[SCTV (Indonesia)|SCTV Music Awards]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.liputan6.com/showbiz/read/2954291/dua-lipa-hibur-sctv-music-awards-2017|title=Dua Lipa Hibur SCTV Music Awards 2017|last=Liputan6.com|date=16 May 2017|work=[[Liputan 6]]|language=id|access-date=1 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220213185154/https://www.liputan6.com/showbiz/read/2954291/dua-lipa-hibur-sctv-music-awards-2017?page=1|archive-date=13 February 2022|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.liputan6.com/showbiz/read/2954108/artis-internasional-dua-lipa-ramaikan-sctv-music-awards-2017|title=Artis Internasional Dua Lipa Ramaikan SCTV Music Awards 2017|last=Liputan6.com|date=16 May 2017|work=[[Liputan 6]]|language=id|access-date=1 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220213185152/https://www.liputan6.com/showbiz/read/2954108/artis-internasional-dua-lipa-ramaikan-sctv-music-awards-2017|archive-date=13 February 2022|url-status=live}}</ref> Lipa's first album ''[[Dua Lipa (album)|Dua Lipa]]'' was released on 2 June 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idolator.com/7643997/dua-lipa-debut-album-cover-art|title=Dua Lipa Reveals Cover Art For Self-Titled Album|last=Sonis|first=Rachel|date=24 August 2016|publisher=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|access-date=24 August 2016|archive-url=https://archive.today/20161107163353/http://www.idolator.com/7643997/dua-lipa-debut-album-cover-art|archive-date=7 November 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Its sixth single, "[[New Rules]]", released in the following month, became Lipa's first number one in the UK,<ref name="UK" /> and the first by a female solo artist to reach the top in the UK since [[Adele]]'s "[[Hello (Adele song)|Hello]]" in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/dua-lipas-new-rules-becomes-the-first-solo-female-uk-number-1-single-since-adele-s-hello-this-means-a-lot-__19978/|title=Dua Lipa's New Rules becomes the first solo female UK Number 1 single since Adele's Hello: 'This means a lot'|last=Copsey|first=Rob|date=18 August 2017|publisher=Official Charts Company|access-date=19 August 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171129042946/http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/dua-lipas-new-rules-becomes-the-first-solo-female-uk-number-1-single-since-adele-s-hello-this-means-a-lot-__19978/|archive-date=29 November 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> Her best-selling single to date, the song also charted in the top ten of other countries, including number two in Australia, number six in the US, and number seven in Canada. {{As of|2024}}, the music video has streamed over three billion views on YouTube.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Denis |first=Kyle |date=31 January 2024 |title=Dua Lipa's 'New Rules' Music Video Dances Past 3 Billion Views on YouTube |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/dua-lipa-new-rules-passes-3-billion-views-youtube-1235593954/ |access-date=24 February 2024 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US |archive-date=5 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240205072923/https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/dua-lipa-new-rules-passes-3-billion-views-youtube-1235593954/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8093297/ed-sheeran-beyonce-perfect-number-one-fifth-week-hot-100|title=Ed Sheeran & Beyonce's 'Perfect' No. 1 on Hot 100, Camila Cabello's 'Havana' Back Up to No. 2|magazine=Billboard|first=Gary|last=Trust|date=8 January 2018|access-date=9 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180111141316/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8093297/ed-sheeran-beyonce-perfect-number-one-fifth-week-hot-100|archive-date=11 January 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Lipa performed at the [[Glastonbury Festival]] in June.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-pulls-one-biggest-crowds-glastonbury-2017-far-hit-packed-set-2092368 |title=Dua Lipa pulls one of the biggest crowds at Glastonbury 2017 so far with hit-packed set |last=Daly |first=Rhian |date=23 June 2017 |work=NME |access-date=26 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170904034028/https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-pulls-one-biggest-crowds-glastonbury-2017-far-hit-packed-set-2092368 |archive-date=4 September 2017 |url-status=live}}</ref> In July, Lipa performed at the [[We The Fest]], an Indonesian music festival in [[Jakarta]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://kumparan.com/@kumparanhits/persembahan-dua-lipa-untuk-para-korban-patah-hati-di-we-the-fest-2017 |title=Persembahan Dua Lipa untuk Para Korban Patah Hati di We The Fest 2017 |language=id |trans-title=Dua Lipa's Offering for the Victims of Broken Hearts at We The Fest 2017 |date=13 August 2017 |work=Kumparan |access-date=19 October 2018 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20230516015251/https://kumparan.com/kumparanhits/persembahan-dua-lipa-untuk-para-korban-patah-hati-di-we-the-fest-2017/full |archive-date=16 May 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> She performed on [[BBC]]'s ''[[Later... with Jools Holland]]'' in October.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b09dct6n|title=BBC Two - Later... with Jools Holland, Series 51 (Live), Episode 6|website=BBC|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171130091000/https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b09dct6n|archive-date=30 November 2017|url-status=live|access-date=1 December 2017}}</ref> In December, Lipa was named the most streamed woman of 2017 in the UK by [[Spotify]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2017/dec/05/how-dua-lipa-became-the-most-streamed-woman-of-2017-new-rules|title=How Dua Lipa became the most streamed woman of 2017|author=Laura Snapes|date=5 December 2017|work=The Guardian|access-date=6 December 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180116113418/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2017/dec/05/how-dua-lipa-became-the-most-streamed-woman-of-2017-new-rules|archive-date=16 January 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> She had four singles reach [[List of UK top 10 singles in 2017|the UK top 10 in 2017]], with "Be the One", "New Rules", "No Lie", and "[[Bridge over Troubled Water (song)#Artists for Grenfell Tower charity single|Bridge over Troubled Water]]", a charity single for the families of the victims of the [[Grenfell Tower fire]] in London.<ref>{{cite web|title=Official Singles Chart Top 100 {{!}} 23 June 2017 – 29 June 2017|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/charts/singles-chart/20170623/7501/|publisher=Official Charts Company|access-date=11 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180220152257/http://www.officialcharts.com/charts/singles-chart/20170623/7501/|archive-date=20 February 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>

In January 2018, Lipa received nominations in five categories at the [[2018 Brit Awards|Brit Awards]], more nominations than any other artist that year. She was nominated for MasterCard British Album of the Year for ''Dua Lipa'', British Single of the Year and British Video of the Year for "New Rules", [[Brit Award for British Female Solo Artist|British Female Solo Artist]], and [[Brit Award for British Breakthrough Act|British Breakthrough Act]] winning the latter two.<ref name=":2">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-42677246|title=Brit Awards 2018: The winners and nominees|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=13 January 2018|access-date=22 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180223033858/http://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-42677246|archive-date=23 February 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> This was the first time that a female artist had received five nominations.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-brit-awards-history-2219324|title=Dua Lipa has made BRIT awards history|magazine=NME|access-date=1 March 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180514110443/https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-brit-awards-history-2219324|archive-date=14 May 2018|url-status=live|last=Maine|first=Samantha|date=14 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=13 January 2018|last=Savage |first=Mark |title=Dua Lipa makes Brit Awards history |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-42677238 |publisher=[[BBC]] |access-date=7 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181209140550/https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-42677238 |archive-date=9 December 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>

Lipa performed at the awards ceremony held on 21 February at [[the O2 Arena]] in London.<ref name=":2" /> The singer collaborated with American DJ [[Whethan]] on the song "High" for the ''[[Fifty Shades Freed (film)|Fifty Shades Freed]]'' [[Fifty Shades Freed: Original Motion Picture Soundtrack|soundtrack]], released in February 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.youredm.com/2018/01/08/whethan-reveals-details-new-collab-dua-lipa-coming-soon/|title=Whethan Reveals Details On New Collab With Dua Lipa Coming Soon|date=8 January 2018|work=Your EDM|access-date=20 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180121072123/http://www.youredm.com/2018/01/08/whethan-reveals-details-new-collab-dua-lipa-coming-soon/|archive-date=21 January 2018|url-status=live|last=Powell|first=Karlie}}</ref> She started working on new material for her second album in January 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.co.uk/dua-lipa/news/dua-lipa-is-starting-work-on-her-second-album|title=Dua Lipa Is Starting Work On Her Second Album|work=MTV|access-date=1 March 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180112130640/http://www.mtv.co.uk/dua-lipa/news/dua-lipa-is-starting-work-on-her-second-album|archive-date=12 January 2018|url-status=live|date=4 January 2018}}</ref> On 6 April, Lipa and [[Calvin Harris]] released the single "[[One Kiss (song)|One Kiss]]",<ref>{{cite web|title=iTunes – Music – One Kiss – Single by Calvin Harris, Dua Lipa|date=6 April 2018|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/one-kiss-single/1364709432|publisher=[[iTunes Store]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180407201414/https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/one-kiss-single/1364709432|archive-date=7 April 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> which topped the UK Singles Chart on 20 April, making it Lipa's second number one in the chart;<ref>{{cite news|title=Calvin Harris and Dua Lipa depose Drake in UK chart|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-43843110|publisher=BBC|date=20 April 2018|access-date=13 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180514170853/http://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-43843110|archive-date=14 May 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Lipa provided the vocals and is also credited as a writer. The single went on to become the biggest selling song in the UK of 2018 and topped the chart for eight consecutive weeks. She performed in the opening ceremony of the [[2018 UEFA Champions League Final]] in [[Kyiv]] on 26 May.<ref>{{cite news|title=Dua Lipa to Perform at UEFA Champions League Opening Ceremony: 'There'll Be a Whole Lot of Girl Power'|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8455039/dua-lipa-performing-uefa-champions-league-opening-ceremony-soccer|magazine=Billboard|access-date=13 May 2018|date=8 May 2018|archive-url=https://archive.today/20230516153354/https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/dua-lipa-performing-uefa-champions-league-opening-ceremony-soccer-8455039/|archive-date=16 May 2023|url-status=live|last=Cummings-Grady|first=Mackenzie}}</ref> It was reported that Lipa would be releasing collaborations with other artists coming out later in 2018, such as one with [[Mark Ronson]] and [[Diplo]]'s newly formed superduo [[Silk City (duo)|Silk City]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hiphopmagz.com/diplo-and-mark-ronson-debut-silk-city-confirm-dua-lipa-collab-is-coming/|title=Diplo and Mark Ronson Debut Silk City, Confirm Dua Lipa Collab Is Coming|work=HipHop Magz|date=23 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190610111552/http://www.hiphopmagz.com/diplo-and-mark-ronson-debut-silk-city-confirm-dua-lipa-collab-is-coming/|archive-date=10 June 2019|access-date=12 June 2018|url-status=live|last=Cook|first=Eric}}</ref> Ronson later confirmed the song's title would be "[[Electricity (Silk City and Dua Lipa song)|Electricity]]".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/dua-lipas-new-single-electricity-with-mark-ronson-and-diplo-was-written-by-florence-welch-and-romy-from-the-xx__23408/|title=Dua Lipa's new single Electricity with Mark Ronson and Diplo was written by Florence Welch and Romy from The xx|publisher=Official Charts Company|date=17 July 2018|access-date=18 July 2018|last=Copsey|first=Rob|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181103170528/http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/dua-lipas-new-single-electricity-with-mark-ronson-and-diplo-was-written-by-florence-welch-and-romy-from-the-xx__23408/|archive-date=3 November 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> The song was released on 9 September. Lipa was also featured in "If Only", a song from Italian singer [[Andrea Bocelli]]'s sixteenth studio album ''[[Sì (Andrea Bocelli album)|Sì]]''.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8476077/andrea-bocelli-si-album-duets-dua-lipa-ed-sheeran-josh-groban|title=Andrea Bocelli 'Si' Album to Feature Duets With Dua Lipa, Ed Sheeran & More|magazine=Billboard|date=20 September 2018|access-date=6 December 2018|last1=Kaufman|first1=Gil|last2=Regan|first2=Jenny|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180920161350/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8476077/andrea-bocelli-si-album-duets-dua-lipa-ed-sheeran-josh-groban|archive-date=20 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>

[[File:Dua Lipa 02 08 2018 -15 (25884030647).jpg|thumb|Lipa at the [[Hollywood Palladium]] in February 2018 |left|228x228px]]
Lipa performed at the [[2018 Singapore Grand Prix|F1 Singapore Grand Prix]] in September.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/lifestyle/entertainment/dua-lipa-and-martin-garrix-share-the-stage-at-singapore-grand-prix-concert|title=Dua Lipa and Martin Garrix share the stage at Singapore Grand Prix concert|last=Raguraman|first=Anjali|work=[[The Straits Times]] |access-date=19 October 2018|archive-url=https://archive.today/20230516145911/https://www.straitstimes.com/lifestyle/entertainment/dua-lipa-and-martin-garrix-share-the-stage-at-singapore-grand-prix-concert|archive-date=16 May 2023|url-status=live|date=17 September 2018}}</ref> In the same month, Lipa endorsed British car brand [[Jaguar Cars|Jaguar]]'s new electric car, [[Jaguar I-Pace|I-PACE]]. The brand created a remix of Lipa's song "Want To" and launched a service where fans could create their own version of Dua Lipa x Jaguar's song on the Join the Pace website, based on their own driving behaviour or the music they listen to, and share it on social media. According to Lipa's team, Jaguar and Lipa set the world record for the "most remixed song ever".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lbbonline.com/news/jaguar-remixes-dua-lipa-and-invites-fans-to-do-the-same/|title=Jaguar Remixes Dua Lipa and Invites Fans to Do the Same|publisher=Little Black Book|date=3 October 2018|access-date=27 October 2019|archive-url=https://archive.today/20230516144348/https://lbbonline.com/news/jaguar-remixes-dua-lipa-and-invites-fans-to-do-the-same|archive-date=16 May 2023|url-status=live}}</ref> In October, the singer released ''[[Dua Lipa: The Complete Edition]]'', an expanded version of her debut album that includes three new songs, including the aforementioned "Want To", and her previous collaborations with other artists.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/dua-lipa-will-release-a-super-deluxe-edition-of-her-debut-album-featuring-three-new-songs-this-october__23853/|title=Dua Lipa will release a super deluxe edition of her debut album featuring three new songs this October |last=White|first=Jack|work=Official Charts|access-date=25 October 2018|date=4 September 2018|archive-url=https://archive.today/20230516020619/https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/dua-lipa-will-release-a-super-deluxe-edition-of-her-debut-album-featuring-three-new-songs-this-october__23853/|archive-date=16 May 2023|url-status=live}}</ref> This included a collaboration with South Korean girl group [[Blackpink]] called "[[Kiss and Make Up (Dua Lipa and Blackpink song)|Kiss and Make Up]]".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iheart.com/content/2018-09-04-dua-lipa-announces-blackpink-collab-kiss-and-make-up-get-the-details/|title=Dua Lipa Announces BLACKPINK Collab 'Kiss And Make Up': Get The Details|work=iHeart|access-date=23 April 2019|last=Brooks|first=Hayden|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200730044749/https://www.iheart.com/content/2018-09-04-dua-lipa-announces-blackpink-collab-kiss-and-make-up-get-the-details/|archive-date=30 July 2020|url-status=live|date=4 September 2018}}</ref>

=== 2019–2022: ''Future Nostalgia'' ===
In January 2019, Lipa released the single "[[Swan Song (song)|Swan Song]]" as part of the soundtrack to the 2019 film ''[[Alita: Battle Angel]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/music/news/alita-battle-angel-to-feature-new-song-by-dua-lipa-1203092020/|title='Alita: Battle Angel' to Feature New Song by Dua Lipa|date=18 December 2018|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|access-date=19 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190704115438/https://variety.com/2018/music/news/alita-battle-angel-to-feature-new-song-by-dua-lipa-1203092020/|archive-date=4 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/fr/album/swan-song-from-the-motion-picture-alita-battle-angel-single/1449762632|title=Swan Song (From the Motion Picture 'Alita: Battle Angel') – Single by Dua Lipa on iTunes|date=24 January 2019|publisher=[[iTunes Store]]|access-date=26 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230515171201/https://music.apple.com/fr/album/swan-song-from-the-motion-picture-alita-battle-angel-single/1449762632|archive-date=15 May 2023|url-status=live}}</ref> That same month, Lipa stated that she spent the preceding year in the writing process for her second studio album.<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/dua-lipa-grammys-music-2019-779203/|title=Dua Lipa's New Rules for 2019|last=Sheffield|first=Rob|date=16 January 2019|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|access-date=8 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190203114126/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/dua-lipa-grammys-music-2019-779203/|archive-date=3 February 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Lipa commented that the album's sound would be a "nostalgic" pop record that "feels like a dancercise class".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-48880735|title=Dua Lipa reveals nerves about new album|last=Savage|first=Mark|date=5 July 2019|work=[[BBC News]]|access-date=8 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191207135250/https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-48880735|archive-date=7 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In August 2019, Lipa partnered with brand [[Yves Saint Laurent (brand)|Yves Saint Laurent]] to endorse their fragrance Libre.<ref name="newbeautyrules" />

Following the release of its lead single "[[Don't Start Now]]", Lipa's second album, ''[[Future Nostalgia]]'', and its accompanying tour were announced in December 2019.<ref name=":02">{{Cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-announces-2020-uk-arena-tour-and-shares-new-album-title-2582524|title=Dua Lipa announces 2020 UK arena tour and shares new album title|last=Reilly|first=Nick|date=2 December 2019|website=[[NME]]|access-date=2 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220424212219/https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-announces-2020-uk-arena-tour-and-shares-new-album-title-2582524|archive-date=24 April 2022|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.capitalfm.com/artists/dua-lipa/new-song-dont-start-now-album/|title=Dua Lipa's New Song 'Don't Start Now' Will Drop Next Week|website=Capital FM|date=24 October 2019|access-date=31 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191028224826/https://www.capitalfm.com/artists/dua-lipa/new-song-dont-start-now-album/|archive-date=28 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="mtv">{{Cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3148945/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-song/|title=Dua Lipa teaches self-confidence amid a disco hurricane on 'Future Nostalgia'|last=Alston|first=Trey|date=13 December 2019|publisher=[[MTV]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191213231506/http://www.mtv.com/news/3148945/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-song/|archive-date=13 December 2019|access-date=15 December 2019}}</ref> "Don't Start Now" peaked at number two on both the UK Singles Chart and the US ''Billboard'' Hot 100.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.musicweek.com/analysis/read/charts-analysis-tones-and-i-holds-off-dua-lipa-at-singles-summit/078025|title=Charts analysis: Tones And I holds off Dua Lipa at singles summit|last=Jones|first=Alan|website=[[Music Week]]|date=8 November 2019|access-date=12 April 2020|url-access=subscription|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200412195928/https://www.musicweek.com/analysis/read/charts-analysis-tones-and-i-holds-off-dua-lipa-at-singles-summit/078025|archive-date=12 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="US" /> On the former, it earned the longest top 10 stay for a British female artist and the longest top 10 stay without reaching the summit in that chart's history.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/the-songs-that-spent-the-most-weeks-inside-the-official-singles-chart-top-10__29522/|title=The songs that have spent the most weeks inside the Official Singles Chart Top 10|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|last=White|first=Jack|date=1 May 2020|access-date=8 April 2021|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210125082539/https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/the-songs-that-spent-the-most-weeks-inside-the-official-singles-chart-top-10__29522/|archive-date=25 January 2021}}</ref> The song also peaked at number one on the UK Big Top 40 and the US ''Billboard'' Mainstream Top 40 chart.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bigtop40.com/news/dua-lipa-number-1-dont-start-now/|title=Dua Lipa is the UK's Number 1 with 'Don't Start Now'|date=10 November 2019|website=[[The Official Big Top 40]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191213233721/https://www.bigtop40.com/news/dua-lipa-number-1-dont-start-now/|archive-date=13 December 2019|access-date=15 December 2019}}</ref><ref name="PopSongsChartBillboard">{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/pop-songs/2020-02-29|title=Pop Songs Chart {{!}} Week of 29 February 2020|magazine=Billboard|access-date=10 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200407010908/https://www.billboard.com/charts/pop-songs/2020-02-29|archive-date=7 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Lipa's second single leading up to the release of the album was "[[Physical (Dua Lipa song)|Physical]]".<ref name="Billboard01302020">{{Cite magazine|last=Aniftos|first=Rania|date=30 January 2020|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8549726/dua-lipa-physical-listen|title=Dua Lipa Gets 'Physical' in Energetic New Video: Watch|magazine=Billboard|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200207155333/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8549726/dua-lipa-physical-listen|archive-date=7 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> It was released on 30 January 2020 and the song's music video was released a day later.<ref name="Billboard01302020" /> "Physical" debuted at number 60 on the US ''Billboard'' Hot 100.<ref name="TheHot100Billboard">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/hot-100|title=The Hot 100 {{!}} Week of 15 February 2020|magazine=Billboard|access-date=11 February 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200215170056/https://www.billboard.com/charts/hot-100|archive-date=15 February 2020}}</ref> ''Future Nostalgia'' was released on 27 March to widespread critical acclaim,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://uproxx.com/pop/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-release-date-coronavirus/|title=Dua Lipa Emotionally Announces 'Future Nostalgia' Has A New Earlier Release Date|date=23 March 2020|website=Uproxx|access-date=24 March 2020|last=Rossignol|first=Derrick|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221205152021/https://uproxx.com/pop/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-release-date-coronavirus/|archive-date=5 December 2022|url-status=live}}</ref> following the release of the record's third single "[[Break My Heart (Dua Lipa song)|Break My Heart]]" on 25 March.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wxerfm.com/news/articles/2020/mar/23/dua-lipa-bumps-up-album-release-date-to-this-friday-new-track-break-my-heart-out-wednesday/998230/|title=Dua Lipa bumps up album release date to this Friday; new track 'Break My Heart' out Wednesday|author=Midwest Communications|website=104.5 and 96.1 The Point|access-date=24 March 2020|archive-date=24 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324131309/https://wxerfm.com/news/articles/2020/mar/23/dua-lipa-bumps-up-album-release-date-to-this-friday-new-track-break-my-heart-out-wednesday/998230/|url-status=dead}}</ref> The album debuted at number two on the Official [[UK Albums Chart]], 5550 copies behind [[5 Seconds of Summer]]'s [[Calm (album)|''Calm'']].<ref>{{Cite magazine|date=3 April 2020|title=5 Seconds Of Summer Are 'Calm' With Chart-Topping U.K. Debut|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9350719/5-seconds-of-summer-top-uk-chart-calm|access-date=26 July 2020|magazine=Billboard|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210126161616/http://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9350719/5-seconds-of-summer-top-uk-chart-calm|archive-date=26 January 2021|url-status=live|last=Sexton|first=Paul}}</ref> ''Future Nostalgia'' peaked at number one on the Official UK Albums Chart the following week in April 2020, while four of the album's singles entered the top ten of the Official Singles Chart.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/9352729/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-midweek-uk-chart |title=Dua Lipa's 'Future Nostalgia' Is Racing to No. 1 In U.K. |date=7 April 2020 |magazine=Billboard |access-date=9 April 2020 |last=Brandle |first=Lars |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200820014527/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/9352729/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-midweek-uk-chart |archive-date=20 August 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> The album holds the record for having the lowest one-week sales while at the top of the chart in the modern era; when it was number one—the week beginning 15 May 2020—the album had a mere 7,317 sales.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Charts analysis: Dua Lipa returns to summit with historic low sale for No.1 album|work=Music Week|url=https://www.musicweek.com/analysis/read/charts-analysis-dua-lipa-returns-to-summit-with-historic-low-sale-for-no-1-album/079809|access-date=26 January 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210617062708/https://www.musicweek.com/analysis/read/charts-analysis-dua-lipa-returns-to-summit-with-historic-low-sale-for-no-1-album/079809|archive-date=17 June 2021|last=Masterson|first=James|url-status=live|url-access=subscription|date=15 May 2020|quote=Dua Lipa's Future Nostalgia album rebounds back to the top of the charts for its third visit and fourth week in total but does so on a chart sale of a mere 7,317 copies.}}</ref> At the time of the album's release, Lipa became the first British female artist since [[Vera Lynn]] to have three top-ten singles in a single calendar year, with Lynn having three in 1952.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/arts-and-lifestyle/article/dua-lipa-british-vogue-interview|title="I'm Always Like, 'OK, What's Next?'": The Unstoppable Rise Of Dua Lipa |date=4 January 2021 |work=Vogue |access-date=4 January 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210114125525/https://www.vogue.co.uk/arts-and-lifestyle/article/dua-lipa-british-vogue-interview|archive-date=14 January 2021|url-status=live|first=Yomi|last=Adegoke}}</ref> Lipa eventually overrode this record with the single "[[Levitating (song)|Levitating]]", which also peaked within the top ten on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 chart, becoming her third top-ten in the US overall. Lipa's music video for "Physical" was nominated for Best Art Director at the Berlin Music Video Awards in 2020. The art director of the music video is Anna Colomer Nogué.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Berlin Music Video Awards|date=30 April 2021|title=Nominees 2020|url=https://www.berlinmva.com/bmva-nominees-2020/|website=berlinmva.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201020120053/https://www.berlinmva.com/bmva-nominees-2020/|archive-date=20 October 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 27 April 2020, DJ Ben Howell released a remix of her song "[[Hallucinate (song)|Hallucinate]]” with the BBC news theme.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=skK3WoK5Z8A|title=Dua Lipa BBC News Remix by Ben H|website=YouTube.com|date=27 April 2020|access-date=1 July 2023|last=Howell|first=Ben|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230702080010/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=skK3WoK5Z8A|archive-date=2 July 2023|url-status=bot: unknown}}</ref> Created during the height of the coronavirus lockdown in his flat in Glasgow, Scotland,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YIgO_KU4yEs|title=Upload TV - BBC News Theme Dua Lipa Remix Interview - 28th April 2020|website=YouTube.com|date=28 April 2020|access-date=1 July 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210817185850/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YIgO_KU4yEs|archive-date=17 August 2021|url-status=live}}</ref> the remix has garnered more than a million views on YouTube as of July 2023. It was pleasantly received by both Lipa <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-bbc-respond-to-hallucinate-bbc-news-theme-remix-2655377|title=Dua Lipa and BBC respond to fan who remixed 'Hallucinate' with the BBC News theme|website=[[NME]]|date=28 April 2020|access-date=9 August 2020|last=Moore|first=Sam|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200809172702/https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-bbc-respond-to-hallucinate-bbc-news-theme-remix-2655377|archive-date=9 August 2020}}</ref> and BBC Radio 1 DJ Greg James, the latter quipping on Twitter "Ben's made you [the BBC] a new theme tune and it's a certified banger. Please change with immediate effect".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0orUxt-8U5o|title=Dua Lipa and BBC News theme remix goes viral|date=29 April 2020|access-date=1 July 2023|work=Bang Showbiz|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230702085330/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0orUxt-8U5o|archive-date=2 July 2023|url-status=live|via=[[YouTube]]}}</ref>

On 11 August 2020, she was named global ambassador of the French mineral water brand [[Évian]]. Lipa made the announcement on social media, where she stated that "it had been an honor" working with the brand.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Pauly|first=Alexandra|date=12 August 2020|title=Dua Lipa Named Evian Global Brand Ambassador|url=https://hypebae.com/2020/8/dua-lipa-evian-global-brand-ambassador-announcement|access-date=7 September 2020|website=Hypebae|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210121112556/https://hypebae.com/2020/8/dua-lipa-evian-global-brand-ambassador-announcement|archive-date=21 January 2021|url-status=live}}</ref> On 13 August, Lipa released a remix of "Levitating" featuring American artists [[Madonna]] and [[Missy Elliott]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/dua-lipa-madonna-missy-elliott-levitating-remix-1043768/|title=Dua Lipa Recruits Madonna, Missy Elliott for 'Levitating' remix|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|last=Spanos|first=Brittany|author-link=Brittany Spanos |date=13 August 2020|access-date=13 August 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200813223705/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/dua-lipa-madonna-missy-elliott-levitating-remix-1043768/|archive-date=13 August 2020}}</ref> It served as the lead single from ''[[Club Future Nostalgia]]'', a remix collection of ''Future Nostalgia'' tracks by [[the Blessed Madonna]] and [[Mark Ronson]], which was released on 28 August.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/dua-lipa-announces-club-future-nostalgia-the-remix-album-featuring-madonna-gwen-stefani-mark-ronson-and-more__30687/|title=Dua Lipa announces delay to upcoming remix album|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|last=Copsey|first=Rob|date=11 August 2020|access-date=11 August 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200811140830/https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/dua-lipa-announces-club-future-nostalgia-the-remix-album-featuring-madonna-gwen-stefani-mark-ronson-and-more__30687/|archive-date=11 August 2020}}</ref> On 2 October 2020, Lipa released the second remix of "Levitating" featuring American rapper [[DaBaby]]; on the same day, Lipa released the music video for the second remix.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Gallagher|first=Alex|date=2 October 2020|title=Dua Lipa shares new 'Levitating' remix featuring DaBaby|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-shares-new-levitating-remix-featuring-dababy-2767750|access-date=18 November 2020|website=NME|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210126102600/https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-shares-new-levitating-remix-featuring-dababy-2767750|archive-date=26 January 2021|url-status=live}}</ref> On 14 October 2020, Lipa and Belgian singer [[Angèle (singer)|Angèle]] were photographed on the set of a music video.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Angèle et Dua Lipa réunies pour un clip: le duo confirmé?|url=https://www.nrj.fr/artistes/angele/actus/angele-et-dua-lipa-reunies-pour-un-clip-le-duo-confirme-71346546|language=fr|access-date=14 November 2020|archive-date=26 October 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201026014637/https://www.nrj.fr/artistes/angele/actus/angele-et-dua-lipa-reunies-pour-un-clip-le-duo-confirme-71346546|url-status=live|work=[[NRJ]]}}</ref> Later in the month, the singers announced the release of their collaboration, "[[Fever (Dua Lipa and Angèle song)|Fever]]"; it was released on 30 October 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Richards|first=Will|date=30 October 2020|title=Dua Lipa releases new single 'Fever' with Belgian singer Angèle|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-to-release-new-single-fever-with-belgian-singer-angele-this-week-2798665|access-date=14 November 2020|website=NME|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210204230842/https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-to-release-new-single-fever-with-belgian-singer-angele-this-week-2798665|archive-date=4 February 2021|url-status=live}}</ref> It is included on the French re-release of ''Future Nostalgia''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fnac.com/a15170739/Dua-Lipa-Future-Nostalgia-Edition-Francaise-Vinyle-album|title=Dua Lipa – Future Nostalgia (French Edition)|work=[[Fnac]]|access-date=4 December 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211028194648/https://www.fnac.com/a15170739/Dua-Lipa-Future-Nostalgia-Edition-Francaise-Vinyle-album|archive-date=28 October 2021|url-status=live}}</ref> Lipa was featured on "[[Prisoner (Miley Cyrus song)|Prisoner]]", a song from [[Miley Cyrus]]' seventh studio album ''[[Plastic Hearts]]''. The single was released on 19 November 2020 alongside the music video.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Buksbaum|first=Sydney|date=20 November 2020|title=Miley Cyrus and Dua Lipa Take a Sexy, Bloody Road Trip in 'Prisoner' Music Video|url=https://people.com/music/miley-cyrus-dua-lipa-prisoner-music-video/|access-date=26 November 2020|website=People|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201210053237/https://people.com/music/miley-cyrus-dua-lipa-prisoner-music-video/|archive-date=10 December 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> In November it was announced that Lipa would be the musical guest on 19 December episode of ''[[Saturday Night Live]]''.<ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Blistein |first1=Jon |title=Bruce Springsteen, Morgan Wallen, Dua Lipa to Perform on 'Saturday Night Live' |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/bruce-springsteen-morgan-wallen-dua-lipa-saturday-night-live-1095448/ |magazine=Rolling Stone |access-date=27 November 2020 |date=25 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230514024306/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/bruce-springsteen-morgan-wallen-dua-lipa-saturday-night-live-1095448/ |archive-date=14 May 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 27 November, Lipa performed in a livestream concert titled [[Studio 2054]], where she sang various songs from ''Future Nostalgia'', a new unreleased track with [[FKA Twigs]], as well as some previous singles such as "New Rules", "One Kiss" and "Electricity". The event featured many special guests like the Blessed Madonna, Angèle, [[Kylie Minogue]] and [[Elton John]], among others.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Hussey|first=Allison|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/dua-lipas-studio-2054-livestream-heres-what-happened/|title=Dua Lipa's Studio 2054 Livestream: Here's What Happened|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=28 November 2020|access-date=30 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201210032121/https://pitchfork.com/news/dua-lipas-studio-2054-livestream-heres-what-happened/|archive-date=10 December 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> ''Future Nostalgia'' was the most streamed album by a woman (and fifth most streamed album overall) on Spotify in 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://newsroom.spotify.com/2020-12-01/the-trends-that-shaped-streaming-in-2020/|title=The Trends That Shaped Streaming in 2020|work=Spotify For The Record|date=1 December 2020|access-date=1 December 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210119120215/https://newsroom.spotify.com/2020-12-01/the-trends-that-shaped-streaming-in-2020/|archive-date=19 January 2021|url-status=live}}</ref>

[[File:DuaLipaO2020522 (104 of 110) (52052957440) (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|Lipa performing at [[The O2 Arena]], London in May 2022]]
On 11 February 2021, Lipa released a single titled "[[We're Good]]", along with ''[[Future Nostalgia: The Moonlight Edition]]''.<ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Aniftos |first1=Rania |title=Dua Lipa Announces New Song 'We're Good' |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/9520813/dua-lipa-new-song-were-good |magazine=Billboard |access-date=5 February 2021 |date=3 February 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210204125314/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/9520813/dua-lipa-new-song-were-good|archive-date=4 February 2021 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/gb/album/future-nostalgia-the-moonlight-edition/1551178998|title=Future Nostalgia (The Moonlight Edition) by Dua Lipa|date=11 February 2021|publisher=[[Apple Music]] (GB)|access-date=12 February 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211128042729/https://music.apple.com/gb/album/future-nostalgia-the-moonlight-edition/1551178998|archive-date=28 November 2021|url-status=live}}</ref> On 26 February 2021, [[Aleyna Tilki]] released her debut English-language single "Retrograde", co-written by Lipa.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Paine |first=Andre |date=26 February 2021 |title=Turkish superstar Aleyna Tilki teams with Dua Lipa, Sarah Hudson, Clarence Coffee & Diplo for global Warner Music release |url=https://www.musicweek.com/talent/read/turkish-superstar-aleyna-tilki-teams-with-dua-lipa-sarah-hudson-clarence-coffee-diplo-for-global-warner-music-release/082711 |access-date=13 November 2022 |website=[[MusicWeek]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211004134255/https://www.musicweek.com/talent/read/turkish-superstar-aleyna-tilki-teams-with-dua-lipa-sarah-hudson-clarence-coffee-diplo-for-global-warner-music-release/082711 |archive-date=4 October 2021 |url-status=live}}</ref> Lipa released the song "Can They Hear Us" from [[Gully (film)#Soundtrack|the soundtrack]] of the film ''[[Gully (film)|Gully]]'' on 4 June 2021.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2021/music/news/gully-soundtrack-dua-lipa-travis-scott-21-savage-1234988041/|title=Soundtrack to 'Gully' Film Featuring Travis Scott Includes Music by Dua Lipa, 21 Savage, Ty Dolla $ign, More (EXCLUSIVE)|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|last=Shanfeld|first=Ethan|date=3 June 2021|access-date=4 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210604105237/https://variety.com/2021/music/news/gully-soundtrack-dua-lipa-travis-scott-21-savage-1234988041/|archive-date=4 June 2021|url-status=live}}</ref> On 13 August 2021, Lipa worked again with Elton John on the song "[[Cold Heart (Pnau remix)]]", released as the lead single from John's studio album ''[[The Lockdown Sessions (Elton John album)|The Lockdown Sessions]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Skipper|first=Tom|url=https://www.nme.com/news/dua-lipa-and-elton-john-preview-new-collaboration-cold-heart-listen-3016861|title=Watch the video for Dua Lipa and Elton John's mash-up club track 'Cold Heart'|website=NME|date=13 August 2021|access-date=22 October 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220413100345/https://www.nme.com/news/dua-lipa-and-elton-john-preview-new-collaboration-cold-heart-listen-3016861|archive-date=13 April 2022|url-status=live}}</ref> On 15 October, the single reached the number one spot on the UK Singles Chart, becoming Lipa's third song to achieve this feat.<ref>{{cite web|last=Beaumont-Thomas|first=Ben|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2021/oct/15/elton-john-scores-first-no-1-single-in-16-years-ending-15-week-ed-sheeran-run|title=Elton John scores first No 1 single in 16 years, ending 15-week Ed Sheeran run|website=The Guardian|date=15 October 2021|access-date=22 October 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220127172042/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2021/oct/15/elton-john-scores-first-no-1-single-in-16-years-ending-15-week-ed-sheeran-run|archive-date=27 January 2022|url-status=live}}</ref> In February 2022, Lipa launched a weekly lifestyle newsletter entitled ''[[Service95]]'' as well as its accompanying podcast ''[[Service95#Dua Lipa: At Your Service|Dua Lipa: At Your Service]]''.<ref>{{cite magazine|date=3 February 2022|title=Sinéad Burke Talks Accessibility {{!}} The Music Genre Taking Over TikTok {{!}} Hong Kong's Roller Girls|magazine=[[Service95]]|issue=1}}</ref>

On 18 February 2022, a source close to the issue confirmed to ''Variety'' that Dua Lipa had parted ways with her longtime management business, Ben Mawson and Ed Millet's TaP Management. Contrary to other reports, the insider claims that the singer is not currently meeting with other management firms, but she will do so in the future.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Aswad |first=Jem |date=18 February 2022 |title=Dua Lipa Parts Ways With TaP Management |pages=1 |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |url=https://variety.com/2022/music/news/dua-lipa-leaves-tap-management-1235185970/?cx_testId=48&cx_testVariant=cx_undefined&cx_artPos=2#cxrecs_s |access-date=20 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220613105958/https://variety.com/2022/music/news/dua-lipa-leaves-tap-management-1235185970/?cx_testId=48&cx_testVariant=cx_undefined&cx_artPos=2 |archive-date=13 June 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 1 March 2022, [[reggae]] band Artikal Sound System filed a suit against Lipa and her label [[Warner Records]] alleging copyright infringement, asserting similarities between "[[Levitating (song)|Levitating]]" and their 2017 song "Live Your Life".<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Donahue|first=Bill|date=1 March 2022|title=Dua Lipa Accused of Stealing 'Levitating' in New Lawsuit|url=https://www.billboard.com/business/legal/dua-lipa-accused-stealing-levitating-artikal-sound-system-lawsuit-1235037859/|access-date=2 March 2022|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220302125244/https://www.billboard.com/business/legal/dua-lipa-accused-stealing-levitating-artikal-sound-system-lawsuit-1235037859/|archive-date=2 March 2022|url-status=live}}</ref> In June 2023, the suit was dropped with prejudice.<ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Donahue |first1=Bill |title=Dua Lipa's Copyright Accusers Drop 'Levitating' Infringement Lawsuit |url=https://www.billboard.com/business/legal/dua-lipa-levitating-copyright-lawsuit-dropped-1235348897/ |magazine=Billboard |access-date=19 July 2023 |date=7 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230608023517/https://www.billboard.com/business/legal/dua-lipa-levitating-copyright-lawsuit-dropped-1235348897/ |archive-date=8 June 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> A second suit by songwriters [[L. Russell Brown]] and [[Sandy Linzer]] claimed that "Levitating" infringed on their 1979 disco song "[[Dr. Buzzard's Original Savannah Band|Wiggle and Giggle All Night]]".<ref name="Kreps_3 June 2022">{{cite magazine |last=Kreps |first=Daniel |title=Dua Lipa Hit With Second Copyright Lawsuit Over 'Levitating' |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |date=6 March 2022 |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/dua-lipa-second-levitating-lawsuit-1317471/ |access-date=12 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220307070123/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/dua-lipa-second-levitating-lawsuit-1317471/ |archive-date=7 March 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 11 March 2022, Lipa and [[Megan Thee Stallion]] released "[[Sweetest Pie (Dua Lipa and Megan Thee Stallion song)|Sweetest Pie]]" accompanied by its music video.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/megan-thee-stallion-and-dua-lipa-tease-new-song-coming-next-week/|title=Megan Thee Stallion and Dua Lipa Tease New Song Coming Next Week|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|last=Bloom|first=Madison|date=6 March 2022|access-date=12 March 2022|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220306212601/https://pitchfork.com/news/megan-thee-stallion-and-dua-lipa-tease-new-song-coming-next-week/|archive-date=6 March 2022}}</ref> The song marks their first collaboration<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/megan-thee-stallion-dua-lipa-release-new-collaborative-single-this-week-3176351|title=Megan Thee Stallion and Dua Lipa to release new collaborative single this week|website=[[NME]]|last=Daly|first=Rhian|date=6 March 2022|access-date=12 March 2022|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220306220541/https://www.nme.com/news/music/megan-thee-stallion-dua-lipa-release-new-collaborative-single-this-week-3176351|archive-date=6 March 2022}}</ref> and serves as the lead single from Megan's second studio album ''[[Traumazine]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-megan-thee-stallion-and-dua-lipas-fantastical-music-video-for-new-collaboration-sweetest-pie-3180476|title=Watch Megan Thee Stallion and Dua Lipa's fantastical music video for new collaboration 'Sweetest Pie'|website=[[NME]]|last=Singh|first=Surej|date=11 March 2022|access-date=12 March 2022|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220311065319/https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-megan-thee-stallion-and-dua-lipas-fantastical-music-video-for-new-collaboration-sweetest-pie-3180476|archive-date=11 March 2022}}</ref> On 27 May, Lipa collaborated with Calvin Harris and [[Young Thug]] to release "[[Potion (song)|Potion]]", serving as the lead single from Harris's sixth studio album ''[[Funk Wav Bounces Vol. 2]]''. It marked the second collaboration between Harris and Lipa following their 2018 single "One Kiss".<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.co.uk/music/news/calvin-harris-and-dua-lipa-to-team-up-again-on-new-track-potion-17632/|title=Calvin Harris and Dua Lipa to team up again on new track 'Potion'|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|location=United Kingdom|last=Reilly|first=Nick|date=25 May 2022|access-date=27 May 2022|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20220525211305/https://www.rollingstone.co.uk/music/news/calvin-harris-and-dua-lipa-to-team-up-again-on-new-track-potion-17632/|archive-date=25 May 2022}}</ref>

===2023–present: Acting debut and ''Radical Optimism''===
On 26 May 2023, Lipa released "[[Dance the Night]]" as the lead single of the ''[[Barbie (film)|Barbie]]'' [[Barbie the Album|film soundtrack]].<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Rowley |first=Glenn |title=Dua Lipa Teases 'Barbie' Single 'Dance the Night': Here's When It Arrives |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/dua-lipa-barbie-song-dance-the-night-snippet-1235333690/ |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |access-date=23 May 2023 |date=22 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230523094611/https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/dua-lipa-barbie-song-dance-the-night-snippet-1235333690/ |archive-date=23 May 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> Lipa made her acting debut in the movie, portraying Mermaid Barbie.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Aminzadeh |first1=Crystal |title=Dua Lipa Talks New Track "Houdini," Her Role in the 'Barbie' Movie & More |url=https://nowdecatur.com/2023/11/14/dua-lipa-talks-new-track-houdini-her-role-in-the-barbie-movie-more/ |publisher=[[WSOY (AM)]] |access-date=5 December 2023 |date=14 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231205190459/https://nowdecatur.com/2023/11/14/dua-lipa-talks-new-track-houdini-her-role-in-the-barbie-movie-more/ |archive-date=5 December 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> In November 2023, Lipa acquired full ownership of all her songs, music, and publishing rights, in a new deal she completed with her former music publishers, Tap Music. The deal included all of her [[master recordings]] from her entire music catalogue, which by February 2024, had reached 40 billion streams.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Reilly |first=Nick |date=3 November 2023 |title=Dua Lipa secures the rights to her songs in new publishing deal |url=https://www.rollingstone.co.uk/music/news/dua-lipa-secures-the-rights-to-her-songs-in-new-publishing-deal-33960/ |access-date=24 February 2024 |website=Rolling Stone UK |language=en-GB |archive-date=24 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240224035551/https://www.rollingstone.co.uk/music/news/dua-lipa-secures-the-rights-to-her-songs-in-new-publishing-deal-33960/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="Norton2024">{{cite AV media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vC_0nvJBN0E |title=How Dua Lipa Moved to London Alone at 15 |date=23 February 2024 |author=Graham Norton |author-link=Graham Norton |language=en |work=[[The Graham Norton Show]] |via=[[YouTube]] |access-date=2 March 2024 |archive-date=1 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240301194330/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vC_0nvJBN0E |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 9 November 2023, Lipa released the lead single from her third studio album titled "[[Houdini (Dua Lipa song)|Houdini]]".<ref>{{Cite web|title=Dua Lipa announces release of brand new single Houdini, kicking off third-album era|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/dua-lipa-houdini-new-single-third-album-kevin-parker-kate-bush/|access-date=2 November 2023|website=officialcharts.com|archive-date=3 November 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231103040326/https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/dua-lipa-houdini-new-single-third-album-kevin-parker-kate-bush/|url-status=live}}</ref> On the day of its release, she said that [[Kevin Parker (musician)|Kevin Parker]], who produced the song with [[Danny L Harle]], was among her "core collaborators" on the album. ''[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]'' referred to Harle as the co-producer of the record.<ref>{{cite web |title=Tame Impala's Kevin Parker Is 'Core Collaborator' On New Dua Lipa LP |url=https://www.spin.com/2023/11/tame-impala-dua-lipa-houdini/ |website=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]] |access-date=5 December 2023 |date=9 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231110123844/https://www.spin.com/2023/11/tame-impala-dua-lipa-houdini/ |archive-date=10 November 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> The follow-up singles, "[[Training Season]]" and "[[Illusion (Dua Lipa song)|Illusion]]", were released on 15 February 2024 and 11 April 2024, respectively.<ref>{{Cite web |date=25 January 2024 |title=Dua Lipa announces next single 'Training Season' |url=https://diymag.com/news/dua-lipa-training-season |access-date=25 January 2024 |website=DIY |language=en |archive-date=25 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240125203355/https://diymag.com/news/dua-lipa-training-season |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Paul |first1=Larisha |title=Dua Lipa Continues 'Radical Optimism' Countdown With Teaser for New Single 'Illusion' |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/dua-lipa-illusion-single-announcement-1234999066/ |magazine=Rolling Stone |access-date=4 April 2024 |date=4 April 2024 |archive-date=5 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240405010644/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/dua-lipa-illusion-single-announcement-1234999066/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The album titled ''[[Radical Optimism]]'' followed on 3 May 2024.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/dua-lipa-announces-new-album-radical-optimism|title=Dua Lipa Announces New Album ''Radical Optimism''|last=Monroe|first=Jazz|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=13 March 2024|access-date=13 March 2024|archive-date=24 April 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240424234951/https://pitchfork.com/news/dua-lipa-announces-new-album-radical-optimism/|url-status=live}}</ref> She continued her acting career with a starring role in the 2024 [[Spy film|spy]] [[action comedy]] ''[[Argylle]]''.<ref>{{cite web|first=Abid|last=Rahman|title=Apple Releases First Trailer for Matthew Vaughn's Spy Romp 'Argylle'|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/argylle-first-trailer-matthew-vaughns-henry-cavill-dua-lipa-1235603170/|date=28 September 2023|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|access-date=9 March 2024|archive-date=9 March 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240309011955/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/argylle-first-trailer-matthew-vaughns-henry-cavill-dua-lipa-1235603170/|url-status=live}}</ref>

In March 2024, Dua Lipa announced she would do a short tour of European arenas in June of the same year.<ref name=":3">{{Cite web |last=Yates |first=Jonny |date=18 March 2024 |title=Dua Lipa announces 2024 European tour dates and ticket details |url=https://www.thepinknews.com/2024/03/18/dua-lipa-tour-dates-tickets-presale/ |access-date=20 March 2024 |website=PinkNews {{!}} Latest lesbian, gay, bi and trans news {{!}} LGBTQ+ news |language=en-US |archive-date=20 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240320153054/https://www.thepinknews.com/2024/03/18/dua-lipa-tour-dates-tickets-presale/ |url-status=live }}</ref> She is set to perform at the [[Arena of Nîmes]], the [[Waldbühne]] in [[Berlin]] and the [[Pula Arena]],<ref name=":3" /> all of which are [[Amphitheatre|amphitheatres]].

==Fashion ventures==
Lipa has been the cover girl of several magazines.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Dua Lipa – Entertainer Profile|url=https://models.com/people/dua-lipa|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201019040510/https://models.com/people/dua-lipa|archive-date=19 October 2020|access-date=16 February 2021|website=Models.com}}</ref> She signed with [[Next Management|Next Models]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Maggioni|first=Sara|date=7 December 2015|title=Dua Lipa – RedMilk|url=http://redmilkmagazine.com/2015/12/redmilk-meets-dua-lipa/|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170623202019/http://redmilkmagazine.com/2015/12/redmilk-meets-dua-lipa/|archive-date=23 June 2017|access-date=21 February 2021|website=Redmilk}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Next / New York / Dua Lipa|url=http://www.nextmanagement.com/new-york/profile/dua-lipa|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180815103907/http://www.nextmanagement.com/new-york/profile/dua-lipa|archive-date=15 August 2018|access-date=21 February 2021|website=[[Next Management]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Next Models print|url=https://res.cloudinary.com/next-management/raw/upload/v1530563432/pdfs/Dua_Lipa_New_York.pdf|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210221024600/https://res.cloudinary.com/next-management/raw/upload/v1530563432/pdfs/Dua_Lipa_New_York.pdf|archive-date=21 February 2021|access-date=21 February 2021|website=Next Management}}</ref> She was in the cover of the "Boom Boom Tick" editorial for [[Elle (magazine)|''Elle'']]'s January 2016 issue.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Boom Boom Tick – Dua Lipa (Elle US)|url=https://models.com/work/elle-us-boom-boom-tick---dua-lipa/504631|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200730060055/https://models.com/work/elle-us-boom-boom-tick---dua-lipa/504631|archive-date=30 July 2020|access-date=21 February 2021|website=Models.com}}</ref><ref name="formulaic">{{Cite web|last=Olivier|first=Bobby|date=24 December 2015|title=Sick Of Formulaic Pop? Dua Lipa Is Here To Shake Things Up|url=https://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/a32855/dua-lipa-profile/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151225050326/https://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/a32855/dua-lipa-profile/|archive-date=25 December 2015|access-date=16 February 2021|website=Elle}}</ref> In April 2016 she was again in an editorial of ''[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]''.<ref name="press kit" /><ref>{{Cite web|title=Dua Lipa (Elle UK)|url=https://models.com/work/elle-uk-dua-lipa|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200730042458/https://models.com/work/elle-uk-dua-lipa|archive-date=30 July 2020|access-date=20 February 2021|website=Models.com}}</ref> She was on a supplemental cover of [[British Vogue|British ''Vogue'']] in November 2016.<ref name="voguem">{{Cite web|last=Pithers|first=Ellie|date=21 December 2016|title=Vogue Meets Dua Lipa|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/dua-lipa-interview-vogue|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161223142932/https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/dua-lipa-interview-vogue|archive-date=23 December 2016|access-date=11 January 2021|website=[[British Vogue]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=British Vogue November 2016 Supplement Cover|url=https://models.com/work/british-vogue-supplement-2016|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210221125547/https://models.com/work/british-vogue-supplement-2016|archive-date=21 February 2021|access-date=21 February 2021|website=Models.com}}</ref> She starred an editorial for the January 2017 issue of ''[[V (American magazine)|V]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|title=V Magazine {{!}} Dua Lipa|url=https://www.lebook.com/creative/v-magazine-dua-lipa-editorial-2017|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170428065901/https://www.lebook.com/creative/v-magazine-dua-lipa-editorial-2017|archive-date=28 April 2017|access-date=21 February 2021|website=[[Le Book]]}}</ref> In the same month, she was on the cover for issue 102 of ''[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Clash Magazine November 2016 Cover|url=https://models.com/work/clash-magazine-dua-lipa|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210221133526/https://models.com/work/clash-magazine-dua-lipa|archive-date=21 February 2021|access-date=21 February 2021|website=Models.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Clash Issue 102 Dua Lipa|url=https://theclashshop.com/products/copy-of-clash-issue-102-dua-lipa|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210221134418/https://theclashshop.com/products/copy-of-clash-issue-102-dua-lipa|archive-date=21 February 2021|access-date=21 February 2021|website=Clash}}</ref> In March 2017, she became a global ambassador for the American shoe company, [[Foot Locker]], to present women's collections offered by the brand.<ref>{{Cite web|date=14 March 2017|title=Foot Locker: Good Business Figures and Dua Lipa as New Brand Ambassador|url=https://www.ispo.com/en/companies/id_79703746/foot-locker-singer-dua-lipa-meant-to-entice-young-women.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170314181634/https://www.ispo.com/en/companies/id_79703746/foot-locker-singer-dua-lipa-meant-to-entice-young-women.html|archive-date=14 March 2017|access-date=24 February 2021|website=[[Internationale Fachmesse für Sportartikel und Sportmode]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=2017 Annual Report|url=https://investors.footlocker-inc.com/static-files/ff2c557e-7ef9-445f-a30d-d3900be65ab3|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210109230547/https://investors.footlocker-inc.com/static-files/ff2c557e-7ef9-445f-a30d-d3900be65ab3|archive-date=9 January 2021|access-date=24 February 2021|website=Foot Looker, Inc}}</ref> She was in an editorial for ''[[Interview (magazine)|Interview]]'' released in April 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Dua Lipa (Interview Magazine)|url=https://models.com/work/interview-magazine-dua-lipa|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210221135711/https://models.com/work/interview-magazine-dua-lipa|archive-date=21 February 2021|access-date=21 February 2021|website=Models.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Kelsey|first=Colleen|date=29 March 2017|title=Dua Lipa Plays With Boundaries|url=https://www.interviewmagazine.com/music/dua-lipa|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170330002319/https://www.interviewmagazine.com/music/dua-lipa|archive-date=30 March 2017|access-date=21 February 2021|website=[[Interview (magazine)|Interview]]}}</ref> She modeled for an editorial of ''[[Paper (magazine)|Paper]]'', published on 6 June 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Jean|first=Jessica|date=6 June 2017|title=Dua Lipa Is On the Rise|url=https://www.papermag.com/dua-lipa-2434757511.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170606204403/https://www.papermag.com/dua-lipa-2434757511.html|archive-date=6 June 2017|access-date=20 February 2021|website=Paper}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Dua Lipa Is on the Rise (Paper Magazine)|url=https://models.com/work/paper-magazine-dua-lipa-is-on-the-rise|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210221015450/https://models.com/work/paper-magazine-dua-lipa-is-on-the-rise|archive-date=21 February 2021|access-date=20 February 2021|website=Models.com}}</ref> She was featured in the summer 2017 issue of ''[[Teen Vogue]]'' in an editorial titled "Fine Tuned".<ref>{{Cite web|title=The Get Down (Teen Vogue)|url=https://models.com/work/teen-vogue-the-get-down/710051|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210221163008/https://models.com/work/teen-vogue-the-get-down/710051|archive-date=21 February 2021|access-date=21 February 2021|website=Models.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Dua Lipa {{!}} Teen Vogue Summer 2017|url=https://blog.nextmanagement.com/2017/05/19/dua-lipa-teen-vogue-summer-2017/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210221163617/https://blog.nextmanagement.com/2017/05/19/dua-lipa-teen-vogue-summer-2017/|archive-date=21 February 2021|access-date=21 February 2021|website=Next Management}}</ref> She was in an editorial for June 2017 issue of ''[[InStyle]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Dua Lipa (InStyle U.S.)|url=https://models.com/work/instyle-us-dua-lipa|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170715010958/https://models.com/work/instyle-us-dua-lipa|archive-date=15 July 2017|access-date=21 February 2021|website=Models.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Stern|first=Claire|date=15 May 2017|title=Meet Dua Lipa, the British Indie Pop Singer You Need to Know|url=https://www.instyle.com/reviews-coverage/music/meet-dua-lipa|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170521214525/https://www.instyle.com/reviews-coverage/music/meet-dua-lipa|archive-date=21 May 2017|access-date=21 February 2021|website=[[InStyle]]}}</ref> She was in an editorial called "Game Changers" for Fall 2017 issue of ''V''.<ref>{{Cite web|title=V Magazine Fall 2017 – Game Changers|url=https://www.streeters.com/news/v-magazine-fall-2017-game-changers|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210221184049/https://www.streeters.com/news/v-magazine-fall-2017-game-changers|archive-date=21 February 2021|access-date=21 February 2021|website=Streeters}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Game Changers (V Magazine)|url=https://models.com/work/v-magazine-game-changers/756976|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210221184546/https://models.com/work/v-magazine-game-changers/756976|archive-date=21 February 2021|access-date=21 February 2021|website=Models.com}}</ref> She was in the Fall/Winter 2017–18 advertising campaign of the Italian brand Patrizia Pepe,<ref>{{Cite web|date=15 August 2017|title=Patrizia Pepe & Dua Lipa|url=http://inside.patriziapepe.com/2017/bang_bang_advcampaign/|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925234723/http://inside.patriziapepe.com/2017/bang_bang_advcampaign/|archive-date=25 September 2017|access-date=21 February 2021|website=Patrizia Pepe|language=Italian}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=15 August 2017|title=Dua Lipa per Patrizia Pepe|url=https://www.vogue.it/moda/news/2017/08/15/dua-lipa-patrizia-pepe|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170819055505/https://www.vogue.it/moda/news/2017/08/15/dua-lipa-patrizia-pepe|archive-date=19 August 2017|access-date=21 February 2021|website=Vogue|language=Italian}}</ref> as well as recorded a cover of the song "[[Bang Bang (My Baby Shot Me Down)]]" (1966) as a soundtrack for the commercial for the said campaign.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Wass|first=Mike|date=15 August 2017|title=Dua Lipa Is The Face Of Patrizia Pepe, Will Cover 'Bang Bang' For Commercial|url=https://www.idolator.com/7667587/dua-lipa-patrizia-pepe-pics-bang-bang-cover|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210221201252/https://www.idolator.com/7667587/dua-lipa-patrizia-pepe-pics-bang-bang-cover?edg-c=1|archive-date=21 February 2021|access-date=21 February 2021|website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]}}</ref> She was on the cover and appeared in an editorial for November 2017 issue of ''[[Evening Standard]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Riddell|first=Rose|date=20 November 2017|title=Dua Lipa on the cover of Evening Standard Magazine, November 2017.|url=https://www.coupdemainmagazine.com/dua-lipa/13542|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171122232546/https://www.coupdemainmagazine.com/dua-lipa/13542|archive-date=22 November 2017|access-date=21 February 2021|website=Coup De Main}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Dua Lipa (ES Magazine Evening Standard)|url=https://models.com/work/es-magazine-evening-standard-dua-lipa|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210221223809/https://models.com/work/es-magazine-evening-standard-dua-lipa|archive-date=21 February 2021|access-date=21 February 2021|website=Models.com}}</ref> In the same month, she released her second collaboration with the brand Foot Locker for autumn/winter collection.<ref>{{Cite web|date=14 November 2017|title=Foot Locker dévoile sa seconde collaboration avec Dua Lipa|url=https://www.grazia.fr/mode/dua-lipa-et-foot-locker-collab-streetwear-inedite-873042|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116122055/https://www.grazia.fr/mode/dua-lipa-et-foot-locker-collab-streetwear-inedite-873042|archive-date=16 January 2021|access-date=24 February 2021|website=Grazia|language=French}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=15 November 2017|title=Dua Lipa x Foot Locker: la nueva alianza musical del fitness|url=https://www.telva.com/fitness/ropa-deportiva/2017/11/15/5a0c192d22601d04108b465f.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171119000651/https://www.telva.com/fitness/ropa-deportiva/2017/11/15/5a0c192d22601d04108b465f.html|archive-date=19 November 2017|access-date=24 February 2021|website=[[Telva]]|language=Spanish}}</ref> In January 2018, she was part of a promotional clip for an [[Adidas Originals]] campaign called "Original Is Never Finished".<ref>{{Cite web|last=Iredale|first=Jessica|date=22 January 2018|title=Dua Lipa, Playboi Carti and Nick Young Cast in Adidas Originals Campaign|url=https://wwd.com/fashion-news/fashion-scoops/dua-lipa-playboi-carti-and-nick-young-cast-in-adidas-originals-campaign-11114194/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180123052708/https://wwd.com/fashion-news/fashion-scoops/dua-lipa-playboi-carti-and-nick-young-cast-in-adidas-originals-campaign-11114194/|archive-date=23 January 2018|access-date=9 March 2021|website=[[Women's Wear Daily]]}}</ref> She was on the cover of April 2018 issue of ''Teen Vogue''.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Brammer|first=John|date=18 April 2018|title=Dua Lipa Reveals the Fourth 'New Rule' in Our April 2018 Cover Interview|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/dua-lipa-interview-april-2018-cover-new-rules|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180418231823/https://www.teenvogue.com/story/dua-lipa-interview-april-2018-cover-new-rules|archive-date=18 April 2018|access-date=22 February 2021|website=Teen Vogue}}</ref> She was on one of the covers for issue 113 of ''V'' entitled "The Music Issue", published in May 2018 as a limited edition.<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Enos|first=Morgan|date=12 April 2018|title=SZA and Dua Lipa Cover 'V Magazine' Summer Music Issue, Interviewed by Jada Smith and Katy Perry|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8305743/sza-dua-lipa-v-magazine-summer-music-issue-cover|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180413023421/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8305743/sza-dua-lipa-v-magazine-summer-music-issue-cover|archive-date=13 April 2018|access-date=22 February 2021|magazine=Billboard}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=DUA V113: The Music Issue (Limited Edition)|url=https://shop.vmagazine.com/products/dua-v113-the-music-issue-limited-edition|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200810083451/https://shop.vmagazine.com/products/dua-v113-the-music-issue-limited-edition|archive-date=10 August 2020|access-date=22 February 2021|website=V}}</ref> She partnered with the fashion brand Nyden on a project to create four clothing collections, but it failed and Lipa "discontinued" her work with the brand.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Casely-Hayford|first=Alice|date=24 May 2018|title=Dua Lipa To Collaborate With /Nyden On Capsule Collections|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/dua-lipa-nyden-collaboration|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180524111745/https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/dua-lipa-nyden-collaboration|archive-date=24 May 2018|access-date=24 February 2021|website=British Vogue}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=23 December 2018|title=Dua Lipa 'discontinues' her work with fashion brand Nyden|url=https://www.irishnews.com/magazine/entertainment/2018/12/23/news/dua-lipa-discontinues-her-work-with-fashion-brand-nyden-1514809/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210224053851/https://www.irishnews.com/magazine/entertainment/2