She was on the cover of British ''[[GQ]]'' for May 2018 issue.<ref name="britishgq">{{Cite web|date=28 March 2018|title=Dua Lipa: One billion people can't be wrong|url=https://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/article/dua-lipa-1-billion|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180329050026/https://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/article/dua-lipa-1-billion|archive-date=29 March 2018|access-date=3 February 2021|website=[[GQ]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Graves|first=Shahlin|date=10 April 2018|title=Dua Lipa on the cover of British GQ, May 2018.|url=https://www.coupdemainmagazine.com/dua-lipa/14126|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190511000804/https://www.coupdemainmagazine.com/dua-lipa/14126|archive-date=11 May 2019|access-date=22 February 2021|website=Coup De Main}}</ref> She was in the cover for May 2018 issue of Turkish edition of ''Vogue''.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Vogue Turkey May 2018 Cover|url=https://models.com/work/vogue-turkey-vogue-turkey-may-2018-cover|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191002065448/https://models.com/work/vogue-turkey-vogue-turkey-may-2018-cover|archive-date=2 October 2019|access-date=22 February 2021|website=Models.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Denizer|first=Neslihan|date=2 June 2018|title=Dua Lipa: Kim Bu Kız?|url=https://vogue.com.tr/moda/dua-lipa-kim-bu-kiz|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210222022757/https://vogue.com.tr/moda/dua-lipa-kim-bu-kiz|archive-date=22 February 2021|access-date=22 February 2021|website=Vogue|location=Turkey|language=Turkish}}</ref> She was in the cover for June 2018 issue of British edition of ''Elle''.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Graves|first=Shahlin|date=7 May 2018|title=Dua Lipa on the cover of Elle UK, June 2018.|url=https://www.coupdemainmagazine.com/dua-lipa/14328|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180509171510/https://www.coupdemainmagazine.com/dua-lipa/14328|archive-date=9 May 2018|access-date=22 February 2021|website=Coup De Main}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Pometsey|first=Olive|date=3 May 2018|title=Dua Lipa On Life, Love And Female Empowerment|url=https://www.elle.com/uk/life-and-culture/a20071462/dua-lipa-june-elle-2018/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210222024841/https://www.elle.com/uk/life-and-culture/a20071462/dua-lipa-june-elle-2018/|archive-date=22 February 2021|access-date=22 February 2021|website=Elle|location=United Kingdom}}</ref> In October 2018, she was part of an [[Adidas]] campaign called "Here to Create" in which she wore brand clothes.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Elefterin|first=Zoe|date=22 October 2018|title=Dua Lipa Stars in Adidas' 'Here to Create' Campaign|url=https://vmagazine.com/article/dua-lipa-serves-sportswear-with-adidas-women/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181125142449/https://vmagazine.com/article/dua-lipa-serves-sportswear-with-adidas-women/|archive-date=25 November 2018|access-date=9 March 2021|website=V}}</ref> She appeared in a ''Billboard'' editorial called "Grammy Preview" alongside [[Post Malone]] and [[Ella Mai]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Billboard magazine {{!}} Grammy Preview|url=https://www.lebook.com/creative/billboard-magazine-grammy-preview-editorial-2018|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210223135020/https://www.lebook.com/creative/billboard-magazine-grammy-preview-editorial-2018|archive-date=23 February 2021|access-date=23 February 2021|website=Lee Book}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine|date=11 October 2018|title=Dua Lipa, Post Malone & Ella Mai: Photos From the Billboard Cover Shoot|url=https://www.billboard.com/photos/8479003/dua-lipa-post-malone-ella-mai-photos/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181012122300/https://www.billboard.com/photos/8479003/dua-lipa-post-malone-ella-mai-photos/|archive-date=12 October 2018|access-date=23 February 2021|magazine=Billboard}}</ref> She starred the cover for January 2019 issue of British ''Vogue'' and an editorial called "Youth Quake".<ref>{{Cite web|title=British Vogue {{!}} Youth Quake|url=https://www.lebook.com/creative/british-vogue-youth-quake-editorial-2019|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190130061654/https://www.lebook.com/creative/british-vogue-youth-quake-editorial-2019|archive-date=30 January 2019|access-date=22 February 2019|website=Lee Book}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Lukarcanin|first=Emina|date=4 December 2018|title=Dua Lipa Covers British 'Vogue's 'The Future Issue'|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8488607/dua-lipa-british-vogue-cover-photos|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181206102544/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8488607/dua-lipa-british-vogue-cover-photos|archive-date=6 December 2018|access-date=22 February 2021|magazine=Billboard}}</ref> She was the image for the [[Pepe Jeans]] London spring/summer 2019 collection campaign, settling down as the first musician to be global ambassador for the brand.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Devaney|first=Susan|date=26 February 2019|title=Dua Lipa On Making Fashion 'Accessible' And Spreading Kindness in 2019|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/dua-lipa-pepe-jeans-campaign-2019|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190226110535/https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/dua-lipa-pepe-jeans-campaign-2019|archive-date=26 February 2019|access-date=23 February 2021|website=British Vogue}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Van Gaal|first=Czar|date=26 February 2019|title=Dua Lipa Fronts Pepe Jeans London SS19 Campaign|url=https://vmagazine.com/article/dua-lipa-fronts-pepe-jeans-london-ss19-campaign/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190227065834/https://vmagazine.com/article/dua-lipa-fronts-pepe-jeans-london-ss19-campaign/|archive-date=27 February 2019|access-date=23 February 2021|website=V}}</ref> Months later she launched her first-ever [[Capsule wardrobe|capsule]] with the same brand for the autumn/winter collection where she designed clothing inspired by the fashion of the [[1990s in fashion|90s]] and [[2000s in fashion#Early 2000s (2000–2002)|early 2000s]]. She had spent part of her childhood in London and remembered her mother talking to her in a Pepe Jeans store in [[Portobello Road]];<ref name="numero">{{Cite web|last=Letonja|first=Timotej|date=4 December 2019|title=Interview with Dua Lipa x Pepe Jeans London|url=https://www.numeromag.nl/interview-dua-lipa-x-pepe-jeans-london|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206154703/https://www.numeromag.nl/interview-dua-lipa-x-pepe-jeans-london|archive-date=6 December 2019|access-date=23 February 2021|website=[[Numéro]]}}</ref> the collection included [[chain mail]] dresses, "casual" denim outfits and garments based on Lipa's "style" released in September 2019.<ref name="numero"/><ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Ullate|first=Sara|date=4 September 2019|title=El debut de Dua Lipa como diseñadora de la mano de Pepe Jeans London viene cargado de 'glitter' y lencería|url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/es/moda/noticias-moda/g28911139/dua-lipa-pepe-jeans-disenadora-coleccion-glitter/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190905014647/https://www.harpersbazaar.com/es/moda/noticias-moda/g28911139/dua-lipa-pepe-jeans-disenadora-coleccion-glitter/|archive-date=5 September 2019|access-date=24 February 2021|magazine=Harper's Bazaar|language=es}}</ref>

Lipa was on the cover of the May 2019 issue of ''Elle''.<ref name="elle" /><ref>{{Cite web|last=Stuart|first=Juliette|date=9 May 2019|title=Dua Lipa on the cover of Elle US.|url=https://www.coupdemainmagazine.com/dua-lipa/15620|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190509074633/https://www.coupdemainmagazine.com/dua-lipa/15620|archive-date=9 May 2019|access-date=22 February 2021|website=Coup De Main}}</ref> She starred one of the four covers in the first issue and an editorial of the re-launch of ''[[The Face (magazine)|The Face]]'' released in September 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Bramley|first=Ellie|date=4 September 2019|title=The Face is back in print – with Dua Lipa and Harry Styles among the cover stars|url=https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2019/sep/05/the-face-is-back-in-print-with-dua-lipa-and-harry-styles-among-the-cover-stars|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190904232735/https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2019/sep/05/the-face-is-back-in-print-with-dua-lipa-and-harry-styles-among-the-cover-stars|archive-date=4 September 2019|access-date=22 February 2021|website=The Guardian}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Rackham|first=Annabel|date=17 September 2019|title=The Face: Is 2019 the time to launch a new magazine?|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/newsbeat-49714497|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190917144701/https://www.bbc.com/news/newsbeat-49714497|archive-date=17 September 2019|access-date=22 February 2021|website=BBC News}}</ref> She was the cover girl of the October 2019 issue and an editorial for the Spanish edition of ''Vogue''.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Moral|first=Selene|date=20 September 2019|title=Dua Lipa sobre su próximo disco: 'Este año habrá nuevo material'|url=https://los40.com/los40/2019/09/20/moda/1568979695_472599.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200809112541/https://los40.com/los40/2019/09/20/moda/1568979695_472599.html|archive-date=9 August 2020|access-date=22 February 2021|website=LOS40|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Gutiérrez|first=Luis|date=19 September 2019|title=Dua Lipa reescribe las reglas del pop en medio del oscuro romance que es Vogue octubre|url=https://www.vogue.es/moda/articulos/dua-lipa-portada-vogue-octubre-luigi-iango|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190923073339/https://www.vogue.es/moda/articulos/dua-lipa-portada-vogue-octubre-luigi-iango|archive-date=23 September 2019|access-date=22 February 2021|website=Vogue Spain|language=es-ES}}</ref> She starred in a ''Vogue'' sitcom clip set in the 90s titled "Dua's World" where she wore the "best" collections of [[New York Fashion Week]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Curran|first=Sarah|date=28 February 2020|title=Dua Lipa Stars in Her Own Stylish Sitcom For Vogue|url=https://etcanada.com/news/600868/dua-lipa-stars-in-stylish-90s-sitcom-for-vogue/|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229041404/https://etcanada.com/news/600868/dua-lipa-stars-in-stylish-90s-sitcom-for-vogue/|archive-date=29 February 2020|access-date=22 February 2021|website=Entertainment Tonight}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Satenstein|first=Liana|date=28 February 2020|title=Dua Lipa Wears the Best Looks of New York Fashion Week|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/dua-lipa-best-looks-new-york-fashion-week-fall-2020-ready-to-wear|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229003542/https://www.vogue.com/article/dua-lipa-best-looks-new-york-fashion-week-fall-2020-ready-to-wear|archive-date=29 February 2020|access-date=22 February 2021|website=Vogue}}</ref> She released her second design collaboration with Pepe Jeans London for spring/summer 2020 collection inspired by the fashion of [[1980s in fashion#Late 1980s (1987–1989)|late 1980s]] and [[1990s in fashion#Early 1990s (1990–1992)|early 1990s]] whose collection included "oversized" [[blazer]]s, [[Crop top|cropped knitwear]], [[Dress#Bodycon dress|bodycon dresses]], and "metallic" [[miniskirt]]s.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Martín|first=Rafael|date=3 March 2020|title=Dua Lipa se convierte en la nueva musa Pepe Jeans London para su campaña primavera-verano 2020|url=https://www.elle.com/es/moda/noticias/a31207055/dua-lipa-pepe-jeans-primavera-verano-2020/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200730051754/https://www.elle.com/es/moda/noticias/a31207055/dua-lipa-pepe-jeans-primavera-verano-2020/|archive-date=30 July 2020|access-date=23 February 2021|website=Elle|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=3 March 2020|title=Dua Lipa releases her second design collaboration with Pepe Jeans for Spring/Summer 2020.|url=https://fashionunited.nl/nieuws/mode/dua-lipa-releases-her-second-design-collaboration-with-pepe-jeans-for-spring-summer-2020/2020030345008|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210224033625/https://fashionunited.nl/nieuws/mode/dua-lipa-releases-her-second-design-collaboration-with-pepe-jeans-for-spring-summer-2020/2020030345008|archive-date=24 February 2021|access-date=24 February 2021|website=[[FashionUnited]]}}</ref> She was on the cover and an editorial called "True to form" for April 2020 issue of [[Vogue Australia|''Vogue'' Australia]].<ref name="vogueaus" /><ref>{{Cite web|last=Graves|first=Shahlin|date=23 March 2020|title=Dua Lipa on the cover of Vogue Australia, April 2020.|url=https://www.coupdemainmagazine.com/dua-lipa/16507|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200808231924/https://www.coupdemainmagazine.com/dua-lipa/16507|archive-date=8 August 2020|access-date=22 February 2021|website=Coup De Main}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=True to Form (Vogue Australia)|url=https://models.com/work/vogue-australia-true-to-form/1316459|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210222221108/https://models.com/work/vogue-australia-true-to-form/1316459|archive-date=22 February 2021|access-date=21 February 2021|website=Models.com}}</ref>

She appeared in a ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' editorial published in April 2020 to discuss about her second studio album ''Future Nostalgia'' (2020).<ref>{{Cite web|title=Dua Lipa (Rolling Stone)|url=https://models.com/work/rolling-stone-dua-lipa|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210223000218/https://models.com/work/rolling-stone-dua-lipa|archive-date=23 February 2021|access-date=22 February 2021|website=Models.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Freeman|first=Jon|date=22 April 2020|title=Dua Lipa's 'Future Nostalgia' Is the Disco Liberation Soundtrack We Need Now|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-disco-987812/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200424185425/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-disco-987812/|archive-date=24 April 2020|access-date=22 February 2021|magazine=Rolling Stone}}</ref> She was on the cover of the ''Elle'' May 2020 issue and an editorial titled "Dua Lipa Gets Physical",<ref>{{Cite web|last=Wasilak|first=Sarah|date=15 April 2020|title=Dua Lipa Wears Nothing but a Sequined Moschino Guitar For Her Elle Cover|url=https://www.popsugar.com/fashion/photo-gallery/47393685/image/47393711/Dua-Lipa-Elle-Cover-May-2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200423050754/https://www.popsugar.com/fashion/photo-gallery/47393685/image/47393711/Dua-Lipa-Elle-Cover-May-2020|archive-date=23 April 2020|access-date=22 February 2021|website=PopSugar}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Dua Lipa Gets Physical (Elle U.S.)|url=https://models.com/work/elle-us-dua-lipa-gets-physical/1330055|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210223003826/https://models.com/work/elle-us-dua-lipa-gets-physical/1330055|archive-date=23 February 2021|access-date=22 February 2021|website=Models.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Giannini|first=Melissa|date=14 April 2020|title=Dua Lipa on Releasing Future Nostalgia During COVID-19 and Quarantining With Anwar Hadid|url=https://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/a31943034/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-interview/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200415055346/https://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/a31943034/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-interview/|archive-date=15 April 2020|access-date=22 February 2021|website=Elle}}</ref> and months later she was in the cover for its Canadian and British edition.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Giannini|first=Melissa|date=23 June 2020|title=Dua Lipa Is Our Summer 2020 Cover Star!|url=https://www.ellecanada.com/culture/celebrity/dua-lipa-elle-canada-cover-summer-2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200706120050/https://www.ellecanada.com/culture/celebrity/dua-lipa-elle-canada-cover-summer-2020|archive-date=6 July 2020|access-date=22 February 2021|website=Elle|location=Canada}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Giannini|first=Melissa|date=2 July 2020|title=Dua Lipa On Future Nostalgia, Affirmations And Women's Rights|url=https://www.elle.com/uk/life-and-culture/a33009273/dua-lipa-august-2020-elle/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200706141008/https://www.elle.com/uk/life-and-culture/a33009273/dua-lipa-august-2020-elle/|archive-date=6 July 2020|access-date=22 February 2021|website=Elle|publication-place=United Kingdom}}</ref> She was the cover girl for June 2020 issue of ''GQ'' on its British edition.<ref>{{Cite web|title=British GQ June 2020 Covers|url=https://models.com/work/british-gq-british-gq-june-2020-covers|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210223131003/https://models.com/work/british-gq-british-gq-june-2020-covers|archive-date=23 February 2021|access-date=23 February 2021|website=Models.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Levesley|first=David|date=6 May 2020|title=Dua Lipa: 'You can't allow other people's words to affect your growth'|url=https://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/culture/article/dua-lipa-interview-2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200506215853/https://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/culture/article/dua-lipa-interview-2020|archive-date=6 May 2020|access-date=23 February 2021|newspaper=British GQ|publication-place=United Kingdom}}</ref> She was on one of two covers for ''W'' magazine's "The Music Issue" published in September 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|last=De Leon|first=Pauline|date=16 August 2020|title=W Magazine Megan Thee Stallion & Dua Lipa Cover|url=https://hypebae.com/2020/8/w-magazine-megan-thee-stallion-dua-lipa-volume-3-the-music-issue-cover-stars-interviews-release-date|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200909031102/https://hypebae.com/2020/8/w-magazine-megan-thee-stallion-dua-lipa-volume-3-the-music-issue-cover-stars-interviews-release-date|archive-date=9 September 2020|access-date=23 February 2021|website=Hypebae}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=W Magazine Vol. III September 2020 Covers|url=https://models.com/work/w-magazine-w-magazine-september--2020-covers|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201130140814/https://models.com/work/w-magazine-w-magazine-september--2020-covers|archive-date=30 November 2020|access-date=23 February 2021|website=Models.com}}</ref> Lipa released her third design collaboration with Pepe Jeans London for autumn/winter 2020 collection and she stated that it would be her last collaboration with the brand called "Denim decades", which was inspired by every decade since Pepe Jeans started selling denim.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Magnocavallo|first=Fabio|date=15 October 2020|title=Dua Lipa Goes Topless For New Pepe Jeans Ad Campaign|url=https://www.inquisitr.com/6333260/dua-lipa-topless/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201018022350/https://www.inquisitr.com/6333260/dua-lipa-topless/|archive-date=18 October 2020|access-date=11 November 2020|website=[[Inquisitr]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Zavala|first=Cristina|date=16 October 2020|title=Dua Lipa posa en topless para la última campaña de su cápsula para Pepe Jeans|url=https://los40.com/los40/2020/10/16/moda/1602861216_221494.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201021074343/https://los40.com/los40/2020/10/16/moda/1602861216_221494.html|archive-date=21 October 2020|access-date=24 February 2021|website=LOS40|language=Spanish}}</ref>

In November 2020, she signed a multi-year partnership with [[Puma (brand)|Puma]] becoming the global ambassador of the brand.<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Aniftos|first=Rania|date=17 November 2020|title=Dua Lipa Is Puma's New Brand Ambassador|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/lifestyle/9485822/dua-lipa-puma-brand-ambassador/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201118013053/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/lifestyle/9485822/dua-lipa-puma-brand-ambassador/|archive-date=18 November 2020|access-date=24 February 2021|magazine=Billboard}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Smith|first=Alberto|date=17 November 2020|title=Puma signs global pop superstar Dua Lipa|url=https://about.puma.com/en/newsroom/corporate-news/2020/2020-11-17-dua-lipa|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201201114151/https://about.puma.com/en/newsroom/corporate-news/2020/2020-11-17-dua-lipa|archive-date=1 December 2020|access-date=24 February 2021|website=[[Puma (brand)|Puma]]}}</ref> She was on the cover for December 2020 issue of ''[[Attitude (magazine)|Attitude]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Dua Lipa Covers December Issue of Attitude Magazine|url=https://www.pressparty.com/pg/newsdesk/purplepr/view/233280/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210223144619/https://www.pressparty.com/pg/newsdesk/purplepr/view/233280/|archive-date=23 February 2021|access-date=23 February 2021|website=[[Pressparty]]}}</ref> She appeared on the cover for February 2021 issue of British ''Vogue''.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Bear|first=Ally|date=4 January 2021|title=Dua Lipa Graces the Cover of This Month's British Vogue|url=https://961kiss.iheart.com/featured/ally-bear/content/2021-01-04-dua-lipa-graces-the-cover-of-this-months-british-vogue/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210105192620/https://961kiss.iheart.com/featured/ally-bear/content/2021-01-04-dua-lipa-graces-the-cover-of-this-months-british-vogue/|archive-date=5 January 2021|access-date=23 February 2021|website=[[WKST-FM]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Enninful|author-link=Edward Enninful|first=Edward|date=4 January 2021|title=Dua Lipa Covers The February 2021 Issue Of British Vogue|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/news/article/dua-lipa-british-vogue-february-2021|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210104172655/https://www.vogue.co.uk/news/article/dua-lipa-british-vogue-february-2021|archive-date=4 January 2021|access-date=23 February 2021|website=British Vogue}}</ref> In the same month, she was protagonist of the cover for issue 1348 of ''Rolling Stone''.<ref name="rollingstone" /><ref>{{Cite web|date=14 January 2021|title=Dua Lipa es la protagonista de la nueva portada de Rolling Stone|url=https://iheartradio.mx/dua-lipa-es-la-protagonista-de-la-nueva-portada-de-rolling-stone/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210223232717/https://iheartradio.mx/dua-lipa-es-la-protagonista-de-la-nueva-portada-de-rolling-stone/|archive-date=23 February 2021|access-date=23 February 2021|website=[[iHeartRadio]]|language=Spanish}}</ref> She was on the cover for the March 2021 issue of ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'', representing the [[Time 100#Time 100 Next list|100 Next list]] about the "future 100 most influential people in the world".<ref name="billboardtime">{{Cite magazine|last=Kaufman|first=Gil|date=17 February 2021|title=Kylie Minogue Praises 'Shining Star' Dua Lipa in Time 'Next 100 Most Influential People' Essay|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9527021/dua-lipa-time-next-100-most-influential-kylie-minogue-essay/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210217181251/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9527021/dua-lipa-time-next-100-most-influential-kylie-minogue-essay/|archive-date=17 February 2021|access-date=24 February 2021|magazine=Billboard}}</ref><ref name="timelipa">{{Cite magazine|last=Minogue|first=Kylie|date=17 February 2021|title=Dua Lipa Is on the Time100 Next 2021 List|url=https://time.com/collection/time100-next-2021/5937664/dua-lipa/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210217124654/https://time.com/collection/time100-next-2021/5937664/dua-lipa/|archive-date=17 February 2021|access-date=24 February 2021|magazine=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]}}</ref> In the same month, she appeared on the cover of ''[[The New York Times]]'' "Music Issue".<ref>{{Cite web|last=Dresdale|first=Andrea|date=11 March 2021|title=Hits by Dua Lipa, Taylor Swift among 'New York Times Magazine's list of 'Songs that Matter Right Now'|url=http://abcnewsradioonline.com/music-news/2021/3/11/hits-by-dua-lipa-taylor-swift-among-new-york-times-magazines.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210311224138/http://abcnewsradioonline.com/music-news/2021/3/11/hits-by-dua-lipa-taylor-swift-among-new-york-times-magazines.html|archive-date=11 March 2021|access-date=11 March 2021|website=ABC News Radio}}</ref> She designed her outfit at the 63rd Annual Grammy Awards red carpet featuring a dress in collaboration with the brand Versace inspired by the [[Aurora Borealis]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Newbold|first=Alice|date=15 March 2021|title=Dua Lipa's Epic Grammys Versace Dress Twinkled Like The Northern Lights|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/news/article/dua-lipa-grammys-2021|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210318012258/https://www.vogue.co.uk/news/article/dua-lipa-grammys-2021|archive-date=18 March 2021|access-date=18 March 2021|website=British Vogue}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Calvario|first=Liz|date=14 March 2021|title=Dua Lipa on the 'Symbolism' Behind Her 2021 GRAMMYs Look and 'Nuts' 6 Nominations (Exclusive)|url=https://www.etonline.com/dua-lipa-on-the-symbolism-behind-her-2021-grammys-look-and-nuts-6-nominations-exclusive-162262|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210315004225/https://www.etonline.com/dua-lipa-on-the-symbolism-behind-her-2021-grammys-look-and-nuts-6-nominations-exclusive-162262|archive-date=15 March 2021|access-date=18 March 2021|website=Entertainment Tonight}}</ref> She was in a Puma brand campaign called "She Moves Us" in which she designed a shoe called "Mayze" released in April 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|last1=Sotire|first1=Timi|last2=Leekley|first2=Lauren|date=26 February 2021|title=Dua Lipa On Dressing For Confidence, Supporting Girlfriends & Proving Yourself|url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-gb/puma-dua-lipa-2|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210226173503/https://www.refinery29.com/en-gb/puma-dua-lipa-2|archive-date=26 February 2021|access-date=18 March 2021|website=Refinery29}}</ref> In June 2021, Lipa was an announced as the face of [[Versace]]'s Fall-Winter 2021 campaign.<ref>{{Cite web|title=DUA LIPA PRESENTS THE NEW LA GRECA PATTERN|url=https://www.versace.com/gb/en-gb/world-of-versace/stories/advertising-campaigns/versace-fw-2021.html|access-date=25 June 2021|website=Versace|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210625083617/https://www.versace.com/gb/en-gb/world-of-versace/stories/advertising-campaigns/versace-fw-2021.html|archive-date=25 June 2021|url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Dress style and endorsements ===
Dua Lipa has been described by the media as a [[fashion icon]].<ref>{{cite web |date= 23 September 2023 |title= Dua Lipa superstar style fashion essentials |url= https://www.vogue.fr/article/dua-lipa-superstar-style-fashion-essentials/ |access-date= 31 December 2023 |website= Vogue France |archive-date= 17 December 2023 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20231217155343/https://www.vogue.fr/article/dua-lipa-superstar-style-fashion-essentials |url-status= live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date= 23 September 2023 |title= Dua Lipa's 19 Best Outfits Ever Prove She's Pop's Reigning Fashion Girl |url= https://www.instyle.com/dua-lipa-best-outfits-6951699/ |access-date= 31 December 2023 |website= Instyle |archive-date= 19 December 2023 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20231219004401/https://www.instyle.com/dua-lipa-best-outfits-6951699 |url-status= live }}</ref>  For a [[Versace]] dress and [[Bulgari]] diamonds she was rated as one of the "best" dressed celebrities of the [[61st Annual Grammy Awards]] ceremony by various media.<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Fisher|first=Lauren|date=10 February 2019|title=The 10 Best Dressed Celebrities at the 2019 Grammys|url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/celebrity/red-carpet-dresses/g26150095/grammys-best-dressed-2019/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190211111614/https://www.harpersbazaar.com/celebrity/red-carpet-dresses/g26150095/grammys-best-dressed-2019/|archive-date=11 February 2019|access-date=26 February 2021|magazine=Harper's Bazaar}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last1=Huber|first1=Eliza|last2=Li|first2=Michelle|date=11 February 2019|title=Grammys Best Dressed Celebrities on the Red Carpet 2019|url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2019/02/222457/best-dressed-grammys-2019|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190213080132/https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2019/02/222457/best-dressed-grammys-2019|archive-date=13 February 2019|access-date=26 February 2021|website=Refinery29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Jensen|first=Erin|date=10 February 2019|title=Grammys 2019: Lady Gaga, Camila Cabello and more best-dressed stars hit high notes|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/entertainthis/2019/02/10/grammys-2019-best-dressed-celebrities-red-carpet/2832289002/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190211092403/https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/entertainthis/2019/02/10/grammys-2019-best-dressed-celebrities-red-carpet/2832289002/|archive-date=11 February 2019|access-date=26 February 2021|website=[[USA Today]]}}</ref> For her [[Alexander Wang (designer)|Alexander Wang]] dress with 90s style, she was rated as one of the "best" dressed celebrities of the [[62nd Annual Grammy Awards]] ceremony.<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Goldberg|first=Carrie|date=26 January 2020|title=Best Dressed Celebrities at the Grammys 2020|url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/celebrity/red-carpet-dresses/g30647540/grammys-best-dressed-2020/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127123832/https://www.harpersbazaar.com/celebrity/red-carpet-dresses/g30647540/grammys-best-dressed-2020/|archive-date=27 January 2020|access-date=26 February 2021|magazine=Harper's Bazaar}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Okwodu|first=Janelle|date=27 January 2020|title=Grammys 2020: The Best Dressed Celebrities on the Red Carpet|url=https://www.vogue.com/vogueworld/slideshow/grammy-awards-2020-best-dressed|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127122503/https://www.vogue.com/vogueworld/slideshow/grammy-awards-2020-best-dressed|archive-date=27 January 2020|access-date=26 January 2021|website=Vogue}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=2020 Grammys: fashion hits and misses|url=https://www.latimes.com/lifestyle/gallery/grammys-2020-best-worst-dressed-gallery|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230507151627/https://www.latimes.com/lifestyle/gallery/grammys-2020-best-worst-dressed-gallery|archive-date=7 May 2023|access-date=26 February 2021|website=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=27 January 2020 }}</ref> For a Versace dress and Bulgari jewelry she was rated as one of the "best" dressed celebrities of the [[63rd Annual Grammy Awards]] ceremony.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Okwodu|first=Janelle|date=14 March 2021|title=The Best Dressed Stars at the 2021 Grammy Awards|url=https://www.vogue.com/slideshow/grammys-2021-vogue-best-dressed|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210315044442/https://www.vogue.com/slideshow/grammys-2021-vogue-best-dressed|archive-date=15 March 2021|access-date=16 March 2021|website=Vogue}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last1=Fidler|first1=Matt|last2=Elan|first2=Priya|last3=Marriott|first3=Hannah|date=15 March 2021|title=Grammys 2021 best dressed: Megan Thee Stallion, Dua Lipa, Harry Styles and more – in pictures|url=https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/gallery/2021/mar/15/grammys-2021-megan-thee-stallion-dua-lipa-harry-style-red-carpet-in-pictures|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210315124404/https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/gallery/2021/mar/15/grammys-2021-megan-thee-stallion-dua-lipa-harry-style-red-carpet-in-pictures|archive-date=15 March 2021|access-date=16 March 2021|website=The Guardian}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last1=Logan|first1=Elizabeth|last2=Cacciatore|first2=Bella|date=14 March 2021|title=Grammys 2021 Red Carpet: Here Are the Best-Dressed Stars|url=https://www.glamour.com/gallery/grammys-2021-best-dressed-celebrities|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210316233012/https://www.glamour.com/gallery/grammys-2021-best-dressed-celebrities|archive-date=16 March 2021|access-date=16 March 2021|website=Glamour}}</ref>

She released a limited edition [[lip gloss]] called "Cremesheen Glass" in collaboration with [[MAC Cosmetics]] for its campaign called "Future Forward".<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Saunders|first=Nicole|date=9 March 2017|title=Justine Skye, Dua Lipa and Lee Hi Front MAC Cosmetics Future Forward Campaign: Exclusive|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/lifestyle/7710369/justine-skye-dua-lipa-and-lee-hi-new-mac-cosmetics-collection|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170309191127/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/lifestyle/7710369/justine-skye-dua-lipa-and-lee-hi-new-mac-cosmetics-collection|archive-date=9 March 2017|access-date=10 March 2021|magazine=Billboard}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Monroe|first=Ian|date=25 May 2017|title=Dua Lipa's MAC Cosmetics Collaboration Is Here|url=https://vmagazine.com/article/dua-lipas-mac-cosmetics-collaboration/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170525215310/https://vmagazine.com/article/dua-lipas-mac-cosmetics-collaboration/|archive-date=25 May 2017|access-date=10 March 2021|website=V}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Levinson|first=Lauren|date=25 May 2017|title=Pop Star Dua Lipa Talks About Creating a Unicorn Lip Gloss For MAC|url=https://www.popsugar.com/beauty/MAC-Dua-Lipa-Lip-Gloss-43576195|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170525224144/https://www.popsugar.com/beauty/MAC-Dua-Lipa-Lip-Gloss-43576195|archive-date=25 May 2017|access-date=10 March 2017|website=PopSugar}}</ref> She became the face of a perfume called "Libre" for a [[Yves Saint Laurent (brand)|Yves Saint Laurent]] campaign launched in September 2019 for which she recorded a promo cover of the song "[[I'm Free (Rolling Stones song)|I'm Free]]" (1965) featured in advertisements for Lipa's campaigns with the brand.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Smith|first=Erica|date=4 June 2019|title=Dua Lipa's Face Has a New Job|url=https://www.thecut.com/2019/06/dua-lipa-ysl-beauty-ambassador-fragrance.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190604165902/https://www.thecut.com/2019/06/dua-lipa-ysl-beauty-ambassador-fragrance.html|archive-date=4 June 2019|access-date=17 March 2021|website=The Cut}}</ref><ref name="newbeautyrules">{{Cite web|last=Hanra|first=Hanna|date=1 August 2019|title=New Beauty Rules: Dua Lipa Is the Face of Yves Saint Laurent's Latest Fragrance|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/dua-lipa-yves-saint-laurent-libre-fragrance|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230426012419/https://www.vogue.com/article/dua-lipa-yves-saint-laurent-libre-fragrance|archive-date=26 April 2023|access-date=17 March 2021|website=Vogue}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-ca/2019/09/8403047/dua-lipas-newest-gig-is-all-about-freedom|title=Dua Lipa Talks Freedom & YSL's New Fragrance Libre|website=[[Refinery29]]|last=Sasso|first=Samantha|date=13 September 2019|access-date=10 March 2021|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210113120719/https://www.refinery29.com/en-ca/2019/09/8403047/dua-lipas-newest-gig-is-all-about-freedom|archive-date=13 January 2021}}</ref> Later she was the face of a new version of the same perfume called "Libre Intense".<ref>{{Cite web|date=29 September 2020|title=Libre Eau de parfum intense: Nova dišava hiše Yves Saint Laurent|url=https://www.grazia.si/libre-eau-de-parfum-intense-nova-disava-hise-yves-saint-laurent/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210122082919/https://www.grazia.si/libre-eau-de-parfum-intense-nova-disava-hise-yves-saint-laurent/|archive-date=22 January 2021|access-date=17 March 2021|website=Grazia|language=Slovenian}}</ref> She became an ambassador for the mineral water brand [[Évian]] in July 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|date=12 August 2020|title=Dua Lipa Shared a Sexy Selfie to Celebrate Her Role as Evian's New Global Ambassador|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/dua-lipa-shared-a-sexy-selfie-to-celebrate-her-role-as-evians-global-ambassador/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200922023944/https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/dua-lipa-shared-a-sexy-selfie-to-celebrate-her-role-as-evians-global-ambassador/|archive-date=22 September 2020|access-date=9 March 2021|website=[[US Weekly]]}}</ref> In March 2021 she performed an [[a cappella]] of her song "Levitating" (2020) for an advertisement for the "Drink True" campaign of the brand Évian.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Dresdale|first=Andrea|date=9 March 2021|title=Hear Dua Lipa sing 'Levitating' a cappella in new Evian commercial|url=http://abcnewsradioonline.com/music-news/2021/3/9/hear-dua-lipa-sing-levitating-a-cappella-in-new-evian-commer.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210309174030/http://abcnewsradioonline.com/music-news/2021/3/9/hear-dua-lipa-sing-levitating-a-cappella-in-new-evian-commer.html|archive-date=9 March 2021|access-date=9 March 2021|website=[[ABC News Radio]]}}</ref>

In February 2024, Dua Lipa was promoted to global ambassador for YSL Beauty.<ref>{{Cite web |title=YSL Beauty names Dua Lipa Global Make-up Ambassador |url=https://cosmeticsbusiness.com/ysl-beauty-dua-lipa-global-make-up-ambassador |access-date=29 February 2024 |website=Cosmetics Business |archive-date=29 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240229142055/https://cosmeticsbusiness.com/ysl-beauty-dua-lipa-global-make-up-ambassador |url-status=live }}</ref> Previously, she had been the face of the "Libre" fragrance since 2019. Her appointment to global ambassador followed a wipe of the YSL Beauty Instagram account.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Mzizi |first=Yola |date=26 February 2024 |title=YSL Beauty Taps Dua Lipa as Global Makeup Ambassador |url=https://www.businessoffashion.com/news/beauty/dua-lipa-ysl-beauty-global-makeup-ambassador/ |access-date=26 February 2024 |website=The Business of Fashion |language=en |archive-date=26 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240226173818/https://www.businessoffashion.com/news/beauty/dua-lipa-ysl-beauty-global-makeup-ambassador/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Modelling===
She made her [[Fashion show#Catwalk|runway]] debut at [[Versace]]'s Spring/Summer 2022 show at [[Milan Fashion Week]], which was soundtracked by tracks from her album ''Future Nostalgia'' (2020).<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Legardye|first=Quinci|date=25 September 2021|title=Dua Lipa Made Her Runway Debut at Versace's Milan Fashion Week Show|url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/celebrity/latest/a37735958/dua-lipa-runway-debut-versace-milan-fashion-week/|access-date=26 September 2021|magazine=Harper's Bazaar|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210927020024/https://www.harpersbazaar.com/celebrity/latest/a37735958/dua-lipa-runway-debut-versace-milan-fashion-week/|archive-date=27 September 2021|url-status=live}}</ref>

==Artistry and influences==
The media have described Lipa as having a [[mezzo-soprano]]<ref>{{Cite web|last=Yorke|first=Ana|date=10 September 2018|title=Lollapalooza Berlin Day 2: Dua Lipa and Imagine Dragons Wow the Crowds, Kraftwerk Demonstrate Their Greatness|url=https://www.popmatters.com/lollapalooza-berlin-2018-day-2-2603697654.html|access-date=26 September 2020|website=Pop Matters|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200814091243/https://www.popmatters.com/lollapalooza-berlin-2018-day-2-2603697654.html?rebelltitem=1#rebelltitem1|archive-date=14 August 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Bein|first=Kat|date=18 July 2018|title=The 10 Best Justin Bieber Covers by Ariana Grande & More|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/8464469/best-justin-bieber-covers|access-date=26 September 2020|magazine=Billboard|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190219163307/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/8464469/best-justin-bieber-covers|archive-date=19 February 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine|date=13 December 2018|title=Billboard's 30 Best Dance/Electronic Songs of 2018: Critics' Picks|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/year-in-music-2018/8489566/best-dance-electronic-songs-2018|access-date=26 September 2020|magazine=Billboard|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210131044331/https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/year-in-music-2018/8489566/best-dance-electronic-songs-2018|archive-date=31 January 2021|url-status=live}}</ref> or [[contralto]]<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.gq.com/story/dua-lipa-is-changing-the-rules-of-pop-music| title=Dua Lipa Is Changing the Rules of Pop Music| work=[[GQ]]| date=24 January 2018| access-date=22 January 2024| first=Erik Madigan| last=Heck| archive-date=16 February 2021| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210216142155/https://www.gq.com/story/dua-lipa-is-changing-the-rules-of-pop-music| url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=https://pitchfork.com/features/lists-and-guides/the-20-best-pop-and-randb-albums-of-2017/| title=The 20 Best Pop and R&B Albums of 2017| work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]| date=19 December 2017| access-date=22 January 2024| first=Katherine| last=St. Asaph| archive-date=10 September 2019| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190910062224/https://pitchfork.com/features/lists-and-guides/the-20-best-pop-and-randb-albums-of-2017/| url-status=live}}</ref> [[Voice type|vocal range]]. Her music is primarily pop, and has also been described as [[disco]], [[House music|house]] and [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]].<ref name="allmusicbio" /><ref>{{cite web|last=Rodriguez|first=Krystal|date=30 March 2021|title=Love To Love Them, Baby: From Donna Summer To Dua Lipa, Meet The Women Singers Who Shaped (And Continue to Shape) Dance Music|url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/news/donna-summer-gloria-gaynor-dua-lipa-aluna-women-singers-who-shaped-dance-music|access-date=30 March 2021|publisher=[[The Recording Academy]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210331203551/https://www.grammy.com/grammys/news/donna-summer-gloria-gaynor-dua-lipa-aluna-women-singers-who-shaped-dance-music|archive-date=31 March 2021|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Independent genre">{{cite web|last=Green|first=Chris|date=27 January 2016|title=Dua Lipa, O2 ABC, Glasgow, review: Jazz-infused songs recall a smoke-filled cabaret bar|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/dua-lipa-o2-abc-glasgow-review-jazz-infused-songs-recall-a-smoke-filled-cabaret-bar-a6836606.html|access-date=22 July 2016|work=[[The Independent]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160513135329/https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/dua-lipa-o2-abc-glasgow-review-jazz-infused-songs-recall-a-smoke-filled-cabaret-bar-a6836606.html|archive-date=13 May 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Stylistically, her music has been described as [[dance-pop]],<ref name="CNN">{{cite web|last1=Gonzalez|first1=Sandra|date=11 February 2019|title=Grammys 2019: Kacey Musgraves has a golden night with album of the year win|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/02/10/entertainment/grammys-2019-highlights/index.html|access-date=11 February 2019|publisher=CNN|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190213072937/https://www.cnn.com/2019/02/10/entertainment/grammys-2019-highlights/index.html|archive-date=13 February 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> [[synth-pop]], [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]],<ref name="Independent genre" /> [[dream pop]],<ref name="digitalspy" /> [[alternative pop]],<ref>{{cite web|last=St. Asaph|first=Katherine|date=19 December 2017|title=The 20 Best Pop and R&B Albums of 2017|url=https://pitchfork.com/features/lists-and-guides/the-20-best-pop-and-randb-albums-of-2017/|access-date=31 October 2019|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171229113816/https://pitchfork.com/features/lists-and-guides/the-20-best-pop-and-randb-albums-of-2017/|archive-date=29 December 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> and [[nu-disco]] subgenres.<ref>{{cite web|last=Muggs|first=Joe|date=28 November 2020|title=Dua Lipa's Studio 2054 – pop sensation locked into the spectacle|url=https://theartsdesk.com/new-music/dua-lipas-studio-2054-pop-sensation-locked-spectacle|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201128234731/https://theartsdesk.com/new-music/dua-lipas-studio-2054-pop-sensation-locked-spectacle|archive-date=28 November 2020|access-date=28 December 2020|website=[[The Arts Desk]]}}</ref> She describes her musical style as being "dark pop".<ref name="guardian1015" /><ref>{{cite news|title=Pop Corner: Dua Lipa saves the Last Dance; Adele is done with James Bond|newspaper=[[The Irish Times]]|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/culture/music/pop-corner-dua-lipa-saves-the-last-dance-adele-is-done-with-james-bond-1.2597650|access-date=2 September 2017|first=Ailbhe|last=Malone|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160415134758/https://www.irishtimes.com/culture/music/pop-corner-dua-lipa-saves-the-last-dance-adele-is-done-with-james-bond-1.2597650|archive-date=15 April 2016|url-status=live|date=4 April 2016}}</ref> She is also noted for singing in a "distinct, husky, low register",<ref name="eveningstandard2" /> and her "sultry" tone.<ref name="formulaic" /> Regarding her songwriting process, Lipa states she usually comes to the studio with a concept and starts developing the song with her co-writers.<ref name="harper" /><ref name="coup">{{cite web|title=Interview: 2016 Must-Know – Dua Lipa|url=https://www.coupdemainmagazine.com/interviews/interview-2016-must-know-dua-lipa|access-date=19 January 2020|website=Coup de Main Magazine|date=22 December 2015|first=Shahlin|last=Graves|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128113904/https://www.coupdemainmagazine.com/interviews/interview-2016-must-know-dua-lipa|archive-date=28 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> She cites [[Kylie Minogue]], [[Pink (singer)|Pink]], [[Nelly Furtado]], [[Jamiroquai]], [[Kendrick Lamar]], and [[Chance the Rapper]] among her musical influences.<ref>{{cite web|last=Wass|first=Mike|date=23 November 2020|title=Dua Lipa & Kylie Minogue Will Perform On 'Studio 2054'|url=https://www.idolator.com/7916227/dua-lipa-kylie-minogue-will-perform-on-studio-2054?view-all&chrome=1|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20201124011246/https://www.idolator.com/7916227/dua-lipa-kylie-minogue-will-perform-on-studio-2054?view-all&chrome=1&edg-c=1|archive-date=24 November 2020|access-date=24 November 2020|website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]}}</ref><ref name="voguem" /><ref>{{cite web|last=Daly|first=Rhian|date=10 April 2020|title=Dua Lipa: 'If somebody told me not to discuss issues I'm passionate about? I wouldn't listen'|url=https://www.nme.com/big-reads/dua-lipa-cover-interview-2020-if-somebody-told-me-not-to-discuss-issues-im-passionate-about-i-wouldnt-listen-2644409|access-date=7 May 2020|website=NME|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200416094637/https://www.nme.com/big-reads/dua-lipa-cover-interview-2020-if-somebody-told-me-not-to-discuss-issues-im-passionate-about-i-wouldnt-listen-2644409|archive-date=16 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> "My idea of pop has been [[Pink (singer)|P!nk]] and [[Christina Aguilera]] and [[Destiny's Child]] and [[Nelly Furtado]]", said Lipa in a ''GQ'' interview in 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Carley|first=Brennan|title=Dua Lipa Is Changing the Rules of Pop Music|url=https://www.gq.com/story/dua-lipa-is-changing-the-rules-of-pop-music|access-date=10 April 2020|website=GQ|date=24 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180312145252/https://www.gq.com/story/dua-lipa-is-changing-the-rules-of-pop-music|archive-date=12 March 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Her second studio album ''[[Future Nostalgia]]'' (2020) was inspired by artists that she listened to during her teens, including [[Gwen Stefani]], [[Madonna]], [[Moloko]], [[Blondie (band)|Blondie]] and [[Outkast]].<ref name=":02" />

Lipa's stage presence was met with criticism in the early stages of her career. A [[YouTube]] comment on her performance of "New Rules" at the 2018 BRIT Awards saying "I love her lack of energy, go girl give us nothing" became an [[internet meme]], subjecting Lipa to ridicule. Lipa credited this criticism as motivation to improve her stage presence.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ahmed |first1=Insane |title=Dua Lipa Explains How The "Go Girl Give Us Nothing" Meme Motivated Her To Improve Her Live Performances |url=https://genius.com/a/dua-lipa-explains-how-the-go-girl-give-us-nothing-meme-motivated-her-to-improve-her-live-performances |website=[[Genius (company)|Genius]] |access-date=17 February 2024 |archive-date=17 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240217074449/https://genius.com/a/dua-lipa-explains-how-the-go-girl-give-us-nothing-meme-motivated-her-to-improve-her-live-performances |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Frank |first1=Jason P. |title=Dua Lipa Goes Girl and Gives Us a Response to Her Memes |url=https://www.vulture.com/2024/01/dua-lipa-memes-go-girl-give-us-nothing.html |website=[[Vulture (website)|Vulture]] |date=16 January 2024 |access-date=17 February 2024 |archive-date=17 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240217074449/https://www.vulture.com/2024/01/dua-lipa-memes-go-girl-give-us-nothing.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Spanos |first1=Brittany |title=Dua Lipa Is Done Being a Mystery |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/dua-lipa-third-album-influences-dating-life-acting-1234945422/ |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |access-date=17 February 2024 |archive-date=17 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240217074449/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/dua-lipa-third-album-influences-dating-life-acting-1234945422/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

== Impact ==
A study conducted by the [[Office for National Statistics]] revealed that the number of people born with the name "Dua" in England and [[Wales]] was 63 in 2017, the year Lipa earned her first UK number one song with "New Rules"; this increased to 126 in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|date=26 August 2020|title=Baby names: Dua Lipa and Kylo Ren inspire parents' choices|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-53905206|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200826111348/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-53905206|archive-date=26 August 2020|access-date=21 March 2021|website=BBC News}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Rawlinson|first=Kevin|date=26 August 2020|title=Baby names: Dua doubles in popularity in England and Wales|url=https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2020/aug/26/baby-names-dua-doubles-in-popularity-in-england-and-wales|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200826171120/https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2020/aug/26/baby-names-dua-doubles-in-popularity-in-england-and-wales|archive-date=26 August 2020|access-date=21 March 2021|website=The Guardian}}</ref> In May 2018, she was included on British ''Vogue''{{'}}s inaugural list of the 25 most influential British women of 2018 with Lipa being the youngest on the list at the age of 22. The magazine's review said her 2017 song "New Rules" is an "anthem of female empowerment [that] laid out a blueprint for modern sex lives", and described her as being a "culture definer".<ref>{{Cite web|last=Moore|first=Sam|date=31 May 2018|title=Dua Lipa named on new list of Britain's most influential women|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-britains-most-influential-women-vogue-25-list-2329507|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180602171058/https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-britains-most-influential-women-vogue-25-list-2329507|archive-date=2 June 2018|access-date=21 March 2021|website=NME}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=31 May 2018|title=The Vogue 25: Meet The Women Shaping 2018|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/vogue-25-the-women-shaping-2018|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180531173743/https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/vogue-25-the-women-shaping-2018|archive-date=31 May 2018|access-date=21 March 2021|website=British Vogue}}</ref>

Lyndsey Havens from ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' credited Lipa as being the protagonist in [[disco]]'s revival in 2020 through her song "Don't Start Now" (2019).<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Havens|first=Lyndsey|date=27 March 2020|title=How Dua Lipa Is Leading The Charge Toward Disco-Influenced Production|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9343687/dua-lipa-lady-gaga-disco-pop-top-40-trend|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200328141957/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9343687/dua-lipa-lady-gaga-disco-pop-top-40-trend|archive-date=28 March 2020|access-date=21 March 2021|magazine=Billboard}}</ref> ''[[People (magazine)|People]]'' magazine called her "the Future of Pop" due to the success of her sophomore album, ''[[Future Nostalgia]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Nelson|first=Jeff|url=https://people.com/music/dua-lipa-talks-new-album-future-nostalgia/|title=Dua Lipa Is the Future of Pop: Inside the Making of Her New Album Future Nostalgia|date=24 April 2020|magazine=People|access-date=16 April 2022|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200801035752/https://people.com/music/dua-lipa-talks-new-album-future-nostalgia/|archive-date=1 August 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> She inspired the French photographer, Hugo Comte, in his first [[photo-book]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Yotka|first=Steff|date=22 February 2021|title=Hugo Comte Releases His First Career Monograph, With Help from Dua Lipa and Bella Hadid|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/hugo-comte-book|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210223005859/https://www.vogue.com/article/hugo-comte-book|archive-date=23 February 2021|access-date=21 March 2021|website=Vogue}}</ref> She was included in ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]''{{'}}s [[Time 100#Time 100 Next list|100 Next list]] on future 100 world's most influential people by Australian singer [[Kylie Minogue]] who in her review called Lipa a "shining star".<ref name="billboardtime" /><ref name="timelipa" /> Mark Sutherland and Jem Aswad from ''Variety'' rated Lipa as being one of the most impactful women in the global entertainment industry.<ref>{{Cite web|last1=Sutherland|first1=Mark|last2=Aswad|first2=Jem|date=5 March 2021|title=From Blackpink to Top Execs: Women in Music Who Have Made an Impact in Global Entertainment|url=https://variety.com/2021/music/news/blackpink-women-in-music-impact-global-1234922072/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210305125714/https://variety.com/2021/music/news/blackpink-women-in-music-impact-global-1234922072/|archive-date=5 March 2021|access-date=21 March 2021|website=Variety}}</ref>

Several [[wax figure]]s of Dua Lipa are found at [[Madame Tussaud's Wax Museum|Madame Tussauds Wax Museums]] in major cities around the world, including at [[Madame Tussauds London]],<ref>{{Cite web|last=Mee|first=Emily|date=16 February 2019|title=Dua Lipa unveils waxwork at Madame Tussauds|url=https://news.sky.com/story/dua-lipa-unveils-waxwork-at-madame-tussauds-11639006|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190216172625/https://news.sky.com/story/dua-lipa-unveils-waxwork-at-madame-tussauds-11639006|archive-date=16 February 2019|access-date=21 March 2021|publisher=Sky News}}</ref> [[Madame Tussauds Amsterdam]],<ref>{{Cite web|last=Hahn|first=Rachel|date=9 April 2019|title=Can You Figure Out What Dua Lipa's Madame Tussauds Wax Figure Is Wearing?|url=https://www.vogue.com/vogueworld/article/dua-lipa-instagram-madame-tussauds-wax-figure-billboard-music-awards|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190411011558/https://www.vogue.com/vogueworld/article/dua-lipa-instagram-madame-tussauds-wax-figure-billboard-music-awards|archive-date=11 April 2019|access-date=21 March 2021|website=Vogue}}</ref> [[Madame Tussauds New York]],<ref name="Tussauds">{{cite web|url=https://www.madametussauds.com/new-york/information/news/first-u-s-based-wax-figure-for-grammy-award-winning-pop-superstar-dua-lipa-launches-at-madame-tussauds-new-york/|title=First U.S.-Based Wax Figure for Grammy Award-Winning Pop Superstar Dua Lipa Launches at Madame Tussauds New York|date=8 December 2022|access-date=4 March 2024|publisher=Madame Tussauds New York|archive-date=4 March 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240304090407/https://www.madametussauds.com/new-york/information/news/first-u-s-based-wax-figure-for-grammy-award-winning-pop-superstar-dua-lipa-launches-at-madame-tussauds-new-york/|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Madame Tussauds Sydney]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.madametussauds.com/sydney/information/news-updates/don-t-start-now-dua-lipa-takes-centre-stage-at-qvb-sydney-flash-mob/|title=Don't Start Now!{{snd}}Dua Lipa takes centre stage at QVB Sydney flash mob|publisher=Madame Tussauds Sydney|access-date=5 April 2024|archive-date=5 April 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240405215718/https://www.madametussauds.com/sydney/information/news-updates/don-t-start-now-dua-lipa-takes-centre-stage-at-qvb-sydney-flash-mob/|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Madame Tussauds Singapore]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.madametussauds.com/singapore/information/latest-news/madame-tussauds-singapore-launches-first-dua-lipa-wax-figure-in-asia/|title=Madame Tussauds Singapore Launches First Dua Lipa Wax Figure In Asia|publisher=Madame Tussauds Singapore|access-date=5 April 2024|archive-date=5 April 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240405215718/https://www.madametussauds.com/singapore/information/latest-news/madame-tussauds-singapore-launches-first-dua-lipa-wax-figure-in-asia/|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Orlando, Florida|Madame Tussauds Orlando]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/dua-lipa-gets-new-madame-tussauds-wax-figure-photo-1235633030/|title=Dua Lipa Gets New Wax Figure at Madame Tussauds Ahead of Her New Album: See the Photo|publisher=Billboard|access-date=5 April 2024|archive-date=5 April 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240405215718/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/dua-lipa-gets-new-madame-tussauds-wax-figure-photo-1235633030/|url-status=live}}</ref> and [[Madame Tussauds Istanbul]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ntv.com.tr/n-life/kultur-ve-sanat/dua-lipanin-balmumu-figuru-madame-tussauds-istanbulda-acildi,kgx75sgy9EaWMPEJqBaMlQ|title=Dua Lipa'nın balmumu figürü Madame Tussauds İstanbul'da açıldı|publisher=Ntv|lang=tr|access-date=5 April 2024|archive-date=5 April 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240405215718/https://www.ntv.com.tr/n-life/kultur-ve-sanat/dua-lipanin-balmumu-figuru-madame-tussauds-istanbulda-acildi,kgx75sgy9EaWMPEJqBaMlQ|url-status=live}}</ref>

== Accolades and achievements ==
{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by Dua Lipa}}
Lipa has received several accolades throughout her career, including five [[Brit Awards]] from thirteen nominations, one [[MTV Video Music Award]] from fifteen nominations, one [[American Music Award]] from six nominations, one [[iHeartRadio Music Award]] from eight nominations, one [[Bambi Awards]] and three [[Grammy Awards]] from eight nominations. Lipa has received two ''[[Guinness World Records]]''; in 2020 for most tickets sold for a livestreamed concert by a solo female artist,<ref>{{Cite web|title=Most tickets sold for a livestreamed concert by a solo female artist (current year)|url=https://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/649129-most-tickets-sold-for-a-livestreamed-concert-by-a-solo-female-artist-current-yea|access-date=19 January 2022|website=[[Guinness World Records]]|date=27 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210505160741/https://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/649129-most-tickets-sold-for-a-livestreamed-concert-by-a-solo-female-artist-current-yea|archive-date=5 May 2021|url-status=live}}</ref> and in 2021 for most monthly listeners on [[Spotify]] for a female artist, but without surpassing the all-time peak achieved by [[Ariana Grande]] the year prior.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Most monthly listeners on Spotify (female)|url=https://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/641496-most-monthly-listeners-on-spotify-for-a-female|access-date=19 January 2022|website=[[Guinness World Records]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211015123507/https://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/641496-most-monthly-listeners-on-spotify-for-a-female|archive-date=15 October 2021|url-status=live}}</ref>

== In the media ==
=== Political views and advocacy ===
[[File:Dua Lipa 02 12 2018 -29 (39056163950).jpg|thumb|260px|left|upright|Lipa raising an [[Rainbow flag (LGBT)|LGBT flag]] in a presentation at the [[Hollywood Palladium]] in [[Los Angeles]] in 2018.<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Daw|first=Stephen|date=13 February 2018|title=Dua Lipa Waves LGBTQ Pride Flag at L.A. Performance|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/pride/8099473/dua-lipa-lgbtq-pride-flag-los-angeles-show-video|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180215055731/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/pride/8099473/dua-lipa-lgbtq-pride-flag-los-angeles-show-video|archive-date=15 February 2018|access-date=28 February 2021|magazine=Billboard}}</ref>]]
Lipa identifies as a [[Feminism|feminist]].<ref name="independent">{{cite web|last1=Barr|first1=Sabrina|date=19 February 2020|title=Dua Lipa: Eight of the Brit Award winner's top feminist moments|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/women/dua-lipa-feminist-moments-brit-awards-2019-speech-new-rules-music-industry-a8784981.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190219082401/https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/women/dua-lipa-feminist-moments-brit-awards-2019-speech-new-rules-music-industry-a8784981.html|archive-date=19 February 2019|access-date=16 August 2020|website=[[The Independent]]}}</ref> She has spoken out against [[sexism]] within the music industry, using [[Social networking service|social media]] to raise awareness of [[Women's rights|women's problems]].<ref name="independent"/><ref name="vogueaus">{{Cite web|last=Faulkner|first=Noelle|date=21 March 2020|title=Dua Lipa on fame, the feminist wave in music and her love-hate relationship with social media|url=https://www.vogue.com.au/celebrity/interviews/dua-lipa-on-fame-the-feminist-wave-in-music-and-her-lovehate-relationship-with-social-media/image-gallery/0ce1d2835722cb05cc72f99842e5f9fc|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323150247/https://www.vogue.com.au/celebrity/interviews/dua-lipa-on-fame-the-feminist-wave-in-music-and-her-lovehate-relationship-with-social-media/image-gallery/0ce1d2835722cb05cc72f99842e5f9fc|archive-date=23 March 2020|access-date=28 July 2020|website=Vogue Australia}}</ref> Lipa has advocated for social equality for the [[LGBT community]].<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Bote|first=Joshua|date=10 October 2018|title=Dua Lipa On the Importance of LGBTQ Activism: 'You Have a Duty to Speak Up'|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/pride/8479252/dua-lipa-lgbtq-activism-interview|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181010201704/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/pride/8479252/dua-lipa-lgbtq-activism-interview|archive-date=10 October 2018|access-date=28 July 2020|magazine=Billboard}}</ref> On 12 February 2018, she raised a [[Rainbow flag (LGBT)|rainbow flag]] while performing her song "[[Be the One (Dua Lipa song)|Be the One]]" in a presentation at the [[Hollywood Palladium]] in [[Los Angeles]] as part of The Self-Titled tour.<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Daw|first=Stephen|date=13 February 2018|title=Dua Lipa Waves LGBTQ Pride Flag at L.A. Performance|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/pride/8099473/dua-lipa-lgbtq-pride-flag-los-angeles-show-video|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180215055731/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/pride/8099473/dua-lipa-lgbtq-pride-flag-los-angeles-show-video|archive-date=15 February 2018|access-date=28 July 2020|magazine=Billboard}}</ref> On the [[2018 Brit Awards]] red carpet she wore a white rose dress in support of [[Time's Up (organization)|Time's Up]] movement.<ref>{{Cite web|date=21 February 2018|title=The Latest: Brits pays tribute to Manchester bomb victims|url=https://apnews.com/article/04ade2484737480b85d4264d067f796b|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206032331/https://apnews.com/article/04ade2484737480b85d4264d067f796b|archive-date=6 February 2021|access-date=5 February 2021|work=Associated Press}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=22 February 2018|title=BRIT Awards: Dua Lipa among singers with white roses to support Time's Up|url=https://canoe.com/entertainment/celebrity/brit-awards-dua-lipa-among-singers-with-white-roses-to-support-times-up|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180222045050/https://canoe.com/entertainment/celebrity/brit-awards-dua-lipa-among-singers-with-white-roses-to-support-times-up|archive-date=22 February 2018|access-date=5 February 2021|website=[[Canoe.com]]}}</ref> Additionally, at the same event, she stated in her acceptance speech for an award her delight at having "women present in these stages" and more "women winning awards".<ref name="ukvogue">{{Cite web|last=Devaney|first=Susan|date=4 January 2021|title=5 Times Dua Lipa Was All About The Sisterhood|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/arts-and-lifestyle/article/dua-lipa-quotes|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210104171242/https://www.vogue.co.uk/arts-and-lifestyle/article/dua-lipa-quotes|archive-date=4 January 2021|access-date=1 February 2021|website=British Vogue}}</ref> She explained that her perception of feminism is not about [[misandry]], but demanding the [[Equal opportunity|same opportunities]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=4 December 2018|title=Dua Lipa Talks Feminism And Body Image in the January Issue Of British Vogue|last=Tsjeng|first=Zing|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/dua-lipa-on-feminism-and-body-image|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181205010104/https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/dua-lipa-on-feminism-and-body-image|archive-date=5 December 2018|access-date=6 February 2021|website=British Vogue}}</ref> In September 2018, some fans were removed by security from a Lipa concert in the [[National Exhibition and Convention Center (Shanghai)|National Exhibition and Convention Center]] of Shanghai for allegedly waving rainbow flags, despite homosexuality being [[Homosexuality in China#Legal status|decriminalized in China]] in 1997.<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Kaufman|first=Gil|date=13 September 2018|title=Dua Lipa Commends Fans Who Waved Rainbow Flags at Shanghai Show: 'I Will Stand By You'|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/pride/8474988/dua-lipa-responds-shanghai-fans-removed-waving-rainbow-flags-instagram|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180914002523/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/pride/8474988/dua-lipa-responds-shanghai-fans-removed-waving-rainbow-flags-instagram|archive-date=14 September 2018|access-date=28 July 2020|magazine=Billboard}}</ref> In response, Lipa said she was "proud" of and "grateful" to the people who showed their [[LGBT pride|pride]] at the show.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Snapes|first=Laura|date=13 September 2018|title=Dua Lipa 'proud' of fans ejected from concert for waving LGBT flags|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/sep/13/fans-removed-dua-lipa-shanghai-concert-china|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180913084950/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/sep/13/fans-removed-dua-lipa-shanghai-concert-china|archive-date=13 September 2018|access-date=28 July 2020|website=The Guardian}}</ref>

In November 2018, Lipa expressed dissatisfaction over the [[Withdrawal from the European Union|withdrawal of the United Kingdom from the European Union]] due to [[Brexit]] because according to her personal experience "no refugee leaves their country without having to."<ref name="fun"/> In June 2019, she made public her support for the ongoing [[2019–2024 Sudanese transition to democracy|Sudanese transition to democracy]] on social media by sharing a blue image that showed the phrase "Stand with [[Sudan]]" where she detailed her rejection of the [[Khartoum massacre]] writing about all "women, men and children fighting for a peaceful transition to democracy".<ref name="sudan">{{Cite web|last=Devaney|first=Susan|date=18 June 2019|title=Rihanna, Naomi Campbell & Dua Lipa Continue To Rally Support in Aid Of #BlueForSudan|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/sudan-crisis-celebrities-social-media-dua-lipa-rihanna|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190618152312/https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/sudan-crisis-celebrities-social-media-dua-lipa-rihanna|archive-date=18 June 2019|access-date=6 February 2021|website=British Vogue}}</ref> She said the event was an attempt to inflict "brutal murder and rape" by [[Rapid Support Forces|government forces]] on those who try to call for democracy, a "violation of the freedom rights" of [[Demographics of Sudan|Sudanese]] citizens for blocking their internet and a "violation of human rights".<ref name="sudan" /> In December of the same year, Lipa endorsed the [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour Party]] led by [[Jeremy Corbyn]] in the [[2019 United Kingdom general election]], comparing the policies of both Labour and [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservatives]] on various issues on social media and affirming that it was "the most important election in a generation".<ref name="labour">{{Cite web|last=Skinner|first=Tom|date=3 December 2019|title=Dua Lipa calls on fanbase to support Labour in general election: 'Your vote counts'|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-calls-on-fanbase-to-support-labour-in-general-election-2583650|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191205011315/https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-calls-on-fanbase-to-support-labour-in-general-election-2583650|archive-date=5 December 2019|access-date=27 September 2020|website=NME}}</ref> She characterized [[Boris Johnson]]'s victory in the election as a "total disaster" for the UK.<ref>{{Cite web|date=13 December 2019|title=Dua Lipa reagon e revoltuar pas fitores së Boris Johnsonit: Çfarë fatkeqësie totale, Britani ti dështove|url=https://telegrafi.com/dua-lipa-reagon-e-revoltuar-pas-fitores-se-boris-jonsonit-cfare-fatkeqesie-totale-britani-ti-deshtove/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191213220741/https://telegrafi.com/dua-lipa-reagon-e-revoltuar-pas-fitores-se-boris-jonsonit-cfare-fatkeqesie-totale-britani-ti-deshtove/|archive-date=13 December 2019|access-date=8 February 2021|website=Telegrafi|language=Albanian}}</ref>

She participated in a short film for an initiative called "Global Feminism", directed by The Circle of [[Annie Lennox]] in association with [[Apple Music]] and released on 7 March 2019 ahead of [[International Women's Day]]. The clip intended to raise awareness of [[misogyny]], rape, and [[violence against women]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kenneally |first=Cerys |date=7 March 2019 |title=Dua Lipa, Ed Sheeran, Biffy Clyro, and more join Annie Lennox's Global Feminism initiative |url=https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/news/latest-news/dua-lipa-ed-sheeran-biffy-clyro-and-more-join-annie-lennoxs-global-feminism |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200615040614/https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/news/latest-news/dua-lipa-ed-sheeran-biffy-clyro-and-more-join-annie-lennoxs-global-feminism |archive-date=15 June 2020 |access-date=28 July 2020 |website=The Line of Best Fit}}</ref> In April 2019, she showed her support for [[LGBT rights in Brunei]] by calling for a boycott against the [[Dorchester Collection|hotel interests of the Sultan of Brunei]], [[Hassanal Bolkiah]], after a penal code [[Capital punishment in Brunei|punishing homosexuality with death]] came into force in [[Brunei]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Jackman |first=Josh |date=4 April 2019 |title=Dua Lipa supports Brunei boycott as gay sex death penalty becomes law |url=https://www.pinknews.co.uk/2019/04/04/dua-lipa-supports-brunei-boycott-gay-sex-death-penalty-law/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190404161124/https://www.pinknews.co.uk/2019/04/04/dua-lipa-supports-brunei-boycott-gay-sex-death-penalty-law/ |archive-date=4 April 2019 |access-date=12 February 2021 |website=Pink News}}</ref> During a [[Billboard Women in Music|''Billboard'' Women in Music]] event, she used her Powerhouse Award acceptance speech to highlight that women "still have a lot to do for real equality" in which she also complained about the "lack of diversity" amongst the artists of the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] and asked for the continued encouragement to "all the young girls out there to be the powerhouses of the future."<ref name="ukvogue" />

Lipa was the headliner party host for the 2020 [[Sydney Gay and Lesbian Mardi Gras]] parade, and was part of the parade,<ref>{{Cite web|date=3 March 2020|title=Dua Lipa Lit Up The 2020 Mardi Gras Official Party|url=https://www.warnermusic.com.au/news/dua-lipa-lit-up-the-2020-mardi-gras-official-party|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200726092922/https://warnermusic.com.au/news/dua-lipa-lit-up-the-2020-mardi-gras-official-party|archive-date=26 July 2020|access-date=12 February 2021|website=Warner Music Group}}</ref> before performing several songs.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Vrajlal|first=Alicia|date=29 February 2020|title=Mardi Gras 2020: Sam Smith's Surprise Float, Dua Lipa Also Joins Parade|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com.au/entry/mardi-gras-2020-parade-sam-smith_au_5e5a46bec5b6beedb4eba7b8|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210212210243/https://www.huffingtonpost.com.au/entry/mardi-gras-2020-parade-sam-smith_au_5e5a46bec5b6beedb4eba7b8|archive-date=12 February 2021|access-date=12 February 2021|newspaper=HuffPost}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Martin|first=Josh|date=29 February 2020|title=Sydney Mardi Gras: Smith appears in surprise float, Dua Lipa performs 'Physical' for the first time|url=https://www.nme.com/en_au/news/music/smith-appears-in-surprise-mardi-gras-float-2616238|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302062649/https://www.nme.com/en_au/news/music/smith-appears-in-surprise-mardi-gras-float-2616238|archive-date=2 March 2020|access-date=5 May 2020|website=NME}}</ref> In July 2020, she signed an open letter to the UK government, being received by the then [[Minister for Women and Equalities]], [[Liz Truss]], to request the banning of [[conversion therapy]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Daly|first=Rhian|date=10 July 2020|title=Dua Lipa, Charli XCX, Elton John and more sign open letter calling for conversion therapy ban|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-charli-xcx-elton-john-sign-open-letter-calling-conversion-therapy-ban-2705644|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200716183718/https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-charli-xcx-elton-john-sign-open-letter-calling-conversion-therapy-ban-2705644|archive-date=16 July 2020|access-date=6 February 2021|website=NME}}</ref>

Lipa is in favor of [[universal health care]] and wondered why people were not protesting about it. In addition, she said that in her country of birth, the United Kingdom, the [[National Health Service]] is considered a "right".<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Aniftos|first=Rania|date=26 October 2020|title=Dua Lipa Gets Real With Sen. Bernie Sanders About 'Completely Free' Health Care in the UK|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9473268/dua-lipa-bernie-sanders-health-care-conversation/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201027031737/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9473268/dua-lipa-bernie-sanders-health-care-conversation/|archive-date=27 October 2020|access-date=6 February 2021|magazine=Billboard}}</ref> In June 2020, Lipa shared an [[Instagram]] post that criticised the [[Israel Defense Forces]]' treatment of [[Palestinians]] and showed Israeli soldiers detaining Palestinian minors.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Frot|first=Mathilde|date=2 June 2020|title=Dua Lipa shares anti-Israel post on Instagram|url=https://www.jpost.com/israel-news/culture/pop-star-dua-lipa-shares-anti-israel-post-on-instagram-629955|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200602081716/https://www.jpost.com/israel-news/culture/pop-star-dua-lipa-shares-anti-israel-post-on-instagram-629955|archive-date=2 June 2020|access-date=20 July 2020|website=[[The Jerusalem Post]]}}</ref> The post also referred to "fake Jews in the [[Israeli government]]" and "fake Christians in the [[Midwestern United States|midwest]] [United States]" who it said had created [[Hamas]] for people to "believe that Hamas is the reason for the decades worth of occupation, oppression, ethnic cleansing, and murder."<ref>{{Cite web|last=Frot|first=Mathilde|date=1 June 2020|title=Dua Lipa criticised over Israel Instagram post referencing 'fake' Jews|url=https://jewishnews.timesofisrael.com/dua-lipa-criticised-over-israel-instagram-post-referencing-fake-jews/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200603101222/https://jewishnews.timesofisrael.com/dua-lipa-criticised-over-israel-instagram-post-referencing-fake-jews/|archive-date=3 June 2020|access-date=4 July 2020|website=[[Jewish News]]}}</ref> An [[Im Tirtzu]] petition signed by over three thousand people was sent to the Israeli Minister of Defense, [[Benny Gantz]], and the Israeli Minister of Culture and Sport, [[Hili Tropper]], demanding that Lipa's songs be banned from [[Army Radio|Israeli Army Radio]] and [[Galgalatz]] due to what Im Tirtzu said was "the incitement against IDF soldiers, the antisemitism, the blood libel, conspiracy theories and the blatant lies in the post" shared by Lipa.<ref>{{Cite web|date=12 June 2020|title=No Anti-IDF Hatred on IDF Radio!|url=https://imti.org.il/en/notoidfhate/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210211021009/https://imti.org.il/en/notoidfhate/|archive-date=11 February 2021|access-date=10 February 2021|website=[[Im Tirtzu]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=3 June 2020|title=Drop Dua Lipa songs from Israeli radio, petition demands|url=https://www.jpost.com/israel-news/petition-calls-for-dua-lipa-songs-to-be-dropped-from-israeli-radio-630138|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200603105156/https://www.jpost.com/israel-news/petition-calls-for-dua-lipa-songs-to-be-dropped-from-israeli-radio-630138|archive-date=3 June 2020|access-date=10 February 2021|website=The Jerusalem Post}}</ref> In response, the Army Radio said that "Galgalatz does not boycott any artist" and "the songs are chosen at the discretion of the editors of each segment."<ref>{{Cite web|last=Tobin|first=Jonathan|date=3 June 2020|title=Thousands call on Israel's Army Radio to drop pop star Dua Lipa|url=https://www.jns.org/thousands-call-on-israels-army-radio-to-drop-pop-star-dua-lipa/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200706165907/https://www.jns.org/thousands-call-on-israels-army-radio-to-drop-pop-star-dua-lipa/|archive-date=6 July 2020|access-date=11 February 2021|website=[[Jewish News Syndicate]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=5 June 2020|title=Right-wing NGO wants singer banned for criticising Israeli soldiers|url=https://www.middleeastmonitor.com/20200605-right-wing-ngo-wants-singer-banned-for-criticising-israeli-soldiers/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200605193226/https://www.middleeastmonitor.com/20200605-right-wing-ngo-wants-singer-banned-for-criticising-israeli-soldiers/|archive-date=5 June 2020|access-date=11 February 2021|website=[[Middle East Monitor]]}}</ref>

In July 2020, Lipa supported a campaign called "Let the Music Play", in which she signed an open letter sent to the then-Culture Secretary, [[Oliver Dowden]], calling for support from the [[government of the United Kingdom]] for the UK's [[live music]] industry's economic loss under the [[COVID-19 pandemic in the United Kingdom|COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Glynn|first=Paul|date=1 July 2020|title=Stars back plea to support UK live music industry|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-53250718|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200702104910/https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-53250718|archive-date=2 July 2020|access-date=11 February 2021|work=BBC News}}</ref>

On 18 July 2020, Lipa shared a post on her Instagram story explaining "[[Political status of Kosovo|why Kosovo is not and will never be Serbia]]", urging followers to sign a petition which called for [[Apple Inc.|Apple]] to include [[Kosovo]] in [[Apple Maps|its mapping services]] as an independent state.<ref name="BBC_2020">{{Cite web|last=Maričić|first=Slobodan|date=19 July 2020|title=Dua Lipa, Kosovo i Srbija: O Eplu, granicama i tome ko je prvi došao|url=https://www.bbc.com/serbian/lat/balkan-53473793|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200902192149/https://www.bbc.com/serbian/lat/balkan-53473793|archive-date=2 September 2020|access-date=20 July 2020|work=BBC News|language=sr}}</ref> The next day, she published on her social media an image of a banner containing an [[Irredentism|irredentist]] map of [[Greater Albania]] that reflected parts of [[Albania]], Kosovo, [[Serbia]], [[Greece]] and [[North Macedonia]] as one nation, appended with the definition of the word "[[Indigenous peoples|autochthonous]]".<ref name="BBCKosovo">{{Cite news|date=21 July 2020|title=Dua Lipa sparks controversy with 'Greater Albania' map tweet|work=BBC News|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-53483451|url-status=live|access-date=11 February 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200721094222/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-53483451|archive-date=21 July 2020}}</ref> As the banner is commonly associated with extreme [[Albanian nationalism]],<ref name="BBCKosovo" /> she received a backlash on social media, where she was accused of [[ethnic nationalism]] and [[fascism]].<ref name="PinkNews">{{Cite web|last=Milton|first=Josh|date=20 July 2020|title=Absolutely nobody had 'Dua Lipa comes out as an Albanian nationalist' on their 2020 bingo cards, so everyone is confused|url=https://www.pinknews.co.uk/2020/07/20/dua-lipa-albanian-greater-albania-nationalism-flag-tweet/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200720212500/https://www.pinknews.co.uk/2020/07/20/dua-lipa-albanian-greater-albania-nationalism-flag-tweet/|archive-date=20 July 2020|access-date=20 July 2020|website=[[PinkNews]]}}</ref><ref name="Axios">{{Cite web|last=Savitsky|first=Shane|date=20 July 2020|title=Dua Lipa courts controversy with tweet backing Albanian nationalism|url=https://www.axios.com/dua-lipa-albanian-nationalism-kosovo-tweet-f2dbf0d3-f044-4f52-a147-cabd39df632c.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200720165125/https://www.axios.com/dua-lipa-albanian-nationalism-kosovo-tweet-f2dbf0d3-f044-4f52-a147-cabd39df632c.html|archive-date=20 July 2020|access-date=20 July 2020|website=[[Axios (website)|Axios]]}}</ref> She later said that her post had been "misinterpreted" by people who promote ethnic separatism, an ideology that she "completely rejects".<ref>{{Cite web|last=O'Connor|first=Roisin|date=21 July 2020|title=Dua Lipa issues statement after controversial Kosovar-Albanians tweet: 'We all deserve to be proud of our ethnicity'|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/dua-lipa-kosovo-albania-tweet-map-heritage-indigenous-apple-maps-a9631326.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200724182622/https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/dua-lipa-kosovo-albania-tweet-map-heritage-indigenous-apple-maps-a9631326.html|archive-date=24 July 2020|access-date=12 February 2021|work=The Independent}}</ref>

In August, she urged her Instagram followers to vote against [[Donald Trump]] in the [[2020 United States presidential election]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=5 August 2020|title=Dua Lipa del kundër Donald Trumpit: Ky njeri është një shaka, mos e votoni atë|url=https://telegrafi.com/dua-lipa-del-kunder-donald-trumpit-ky-njeri-eshte-nje-shaka-mos-e-votoni-ate/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200806191440/https://telegrafi.com/dua-lipa-del-kunder-donald-trumpit-ky-njeri-eshte-nje-shaka-mos-e-votoni-ate/|archive-date=6 August 2020|access-date=11 February 2021|website=Telegrafi|language=Albanian}}</ref>

After endorsing and campaigning for U.S. Senator [[Bernie Sanders]] in the [[2020 Democratic Party presidential primaries|2020 Democratic primaries]], Lipa expressed support for [[Joe Biden]] to become the U.S. president at a virtual event aimed at [[Albanian Americans]] later that year during the general election season, arguing that the [[Kosovo Albanians|Kosovars]] "owed" support to Biden because he was against the [[War crimes in the Kosovo War|massacre and ethnic cleansing]] of [[Albanians]] by having supported the [[NATO bombing of Yugoslavia]].<ref name="Mejdini">{{cite news|last=Mejdini|first=Fatjona|date=30 October 2020|title=Biden Counts on History to Help Win Albanian American Vote|agency=Balkan Insight|url=https://balkaninsight.com/2020/10/30/biden-counts-on-history-to-help-win-albanian-american-vote/|url-status=live|access-date=30 October 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201101010446/https://balkaninsight.com/2020/10/30/biden-counts-on-history-to-help-win-albanian-american-vote/|archive-date=1 November 2020}}</ref> In January 2021, she published a call to her Instagram followers to encourage Kosovo citizens to vote in the [[2021 Kosovan parliamentary election]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=19 January 2021|title=Dua Lipa dhe babai i saj u bëjnë thirrje qytetarëve të Kosovës që të dalin të votojnë më 14 shkurt|url=https://telegrafi.com/dua-lipa-dhe-babai-saj-u-bejne-thirrje-qytetareve-te-kosoves-qe-te-dalin-te-votojne-14-shkurt/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208135525/https://telegrafi.com/dua-lipa-dhe-babai-saj-u-bejne-thirrje-qytetareve-te-kosoves-qe-te-dalin-te-votojne-14-shkurt/|archive-date=8 February 2021|access-date=8 February 2021|website=Telegrafi|language=Albanian}}</ref>

In May 2021, after expressing solidarity for the death of Palestinian civilians due to the [[2021 Israel–Palestine crisis|Israel–Palestine crisis]], Lipa criticised ''[[The New York Times]]'' for publishing an advertisement characterizing her, along with [[Bella Hadid|Bella]] and [[Gigi Hadid]], as [[Antisemitism|antisemitic]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Dua Lipa criticises ad claiming her views on Israeli-Palestinian conflict are antisemitic |last=Brereton |first=Greta |website=[[NME]] |date=23 May 2021 |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-criticises-ad-claiming-her-views-on-israeli-palestinian-conflict-are-antisemitic-2946420 |access-date=6 June 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220214183501/https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-criticises-ad-claiming-her-views-on-israeli-palestinian-conflict-are-antisemitic-2946420 |archive-date=14 February 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref>

In July 2021, through her Sunny Hill Foundation, Lipa joined an initiative that was launched by the Municipality of [[Tirana]], called "Adopt a Kindergarten". The aim of the project was to reconstruct a kindergarten that was severely damaged by the [[2019 Albania earthquake]]. She said, "The kindergarten will be very beautiful and I am very proud that Sunny Hill Foundation is a part of it. Let's see better things for our country. I am very proud to be Albanian."<ref>{{Cite web|date=23 July 2021|title=Dua Lipa in Tirana for reconstruction initiative 'Adopt a Kindergarten'|url=https://euronews.al/en/albania/2021/07/23/dua-lipa-in-tirana-for-reconstruction-initiative-adopt-a-kindergarten/|access-date=15 October 2021|website=euronews.al|publisher=[[Euronews#Secondary franchises|Euronews Albania]]|archive-date=28 October 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211028134449/https://euronews.al/en/albania/2021/07/23/dua-lipa-in-tirana-for-reconstruction-initiative-adopt-a-kindergarten/|url-status=dead}}</ref> The kindergarten was completed in October 2021, and was named "Sunny Hill Kindergarten".<ref>{{Cite instagram|author=Dua Lipa|author-link=Dua Lipa|user=dualipa|postid=CU-R-_osTMN|date=13 October 2021|title=a very proud moment|archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/iarchive/instagram/dualipa/2683661523686077197_2683661139351720042 |archive-date=14 February 2024 |access-date=14 October 2021 |url-status=dead}}</ref>

Lipa has also continuously raised awareness to the detrimental consequences of the [[2021 Taliban offensive|Taliban takeover of 2021]] in Afghanistan through her social media and her lifestyle newsletter [[Service95]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=James |first=Lucy |date=21 February 2022 |title=A Note From Dua |url=https://www.service95.com/a-note-from-dua/ |access-date=2 June 2023 |website=Service95 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230602024603/https://www.service95.com/a-note-from-dua/ |archive-date=2 June 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref>

In August 2022, Lipa was named an [[Honorary Ambassador of Kosovo]] by the [[President of Kosovo]] [[Vjosa Osmani]]. In response, Lipa wrote that it was an "honor and a privilege to be able to represent my country all over the world" and that she supports the right of Kosovans "to [[Visa requirements for Kosovan citizens|visa]] liberalization, freedom to travel and to dream big."<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Dresdale |first1=Andrea|last2=Bernabe |first2=Angeline Jane|date=8 August 2022|title=Dua Lipa named honorary ambassador of Kosovo: 'It's an honour and a privilege'|url=https://goodmorningamerica.com/culture/story/dua-lipa-named-honorary-ambassador-kosovo-honour-privilege-88102795|access-date=9 August 2022|website=ABC News|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220930124717/https://goodmorningamerica.com/culture/story/dua-lipa-named-honorary-ambassador-kosovo-honour-privilege-88102795|archive-date=30 September 2022|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 13 November 2022, Lipa dismissed reports that she was to perform at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup#Opening ceremony|opening ceremony]] of [[2022 FIFA World Cup|that year's FIFA World Cup]], and denied ever being involved in any negotiation to perform, calling out the tournament's host country of [[Qatar]] for [[2022 FIFA World Cup controversies#Human rights issues|human rights violations]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Rathborn |first=Jack |date=13 November 2022 |title=Dua Lipa dismisses reports she will perform at Qatar World Cup |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/world-cup/dua-lipa-world-cup-qatar-b2224134.html |access-date=13 November 2022 |website=[[The Independent]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221207173934/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/world-cup/dua-lipa-world-cup-qatar-b2224134.html |archive-date=7 December 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref>

In October 2023, Lipa signed an open letter for the "[[Artists4Ceasefire]]" campaign alongside 185 other artists, urging President Biden to push for a ceasefire and an end to the killing of civilians amid the [[Israeli invasion of the Gaza Strip (2023–present)|2023 Israeli invasion of the Gaza Strip]], and for a corridor into Gaza to be established for humanitarian aid.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Aniftos |first=Rania |date=25 October 2023 |title=Dua Lipa, Michael Stipe & More Stars Sign Open Letter to President Biden Urging for Ceasefire in Gaza |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/gaza-ceasefire-open-letter-dua-lipa-musicians-1235454451/ |access-date=27 October 2023 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |archive-date=26 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231026165136/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/gaza-ceasefire-open-letter-dua-lipa-musicians-1235454451/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In November 2023, Israeli music duo Ness & Stilla released the single "[[Harbu Darbu]]",<ref>{{cite news |last1=Fiske |first1=Gavriel |title=Hip-hop war anthem reaches number one in Israel |url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/hip-hop-war-anthem-reaches-number-one-in-israel/ |work=The Times of Israel |date=21 November 2023 |archive-date=2 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231202212635/https://www.timesofisrael.com/hip-hop-war-anthem-reaches-number-one-in-israel/ |url-status=live }}</ref> which called for Lipa's death.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Zitser |first1=Joshua |title=Israel's Gen Z is dancing to a war song that celebrates bombing Gaza and names Dua Lipa and Bella Hadid as enemies |url=https://www.businessinsider.com/israel-gen-z-tiktok-harbu-darbu-song-supporting-gaza-bombing-2023-12 |work=Business Insider |date=12 December 2023 |access-date=3 February 2024 |archive-date=20 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231220192549/https://www.businessinsider.com/israel-gen-z-tiktok-harbu-darbu-song-supporting-gaza-bombing-2023-12 |url-status=live }}</ref>

=== Philanthropy ===
She and her father, Dukagjin, co-created the Sunny Hill Foundation in 2016 to raise funds to help people in Kosovo experiencing financial difficulties. In August 2018, Dua Lipa organized a festival to raise money for the foundation called the [[Sunny Hill Festival]]. The then-[[Mayor of Pristina]], [[Shpend Ahmeti]], awarded her the Pristina Key, the first time one had been awarded.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Butler|first=Will|date=11 August 2018|title=Dua Lipa receives the first ever key to the capital of Kosovo|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-receives-first-ever-key-prishtina-kosovo-2365499|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210207060539/https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-receives-first-ever-key-prishtina-kosovo-2365499|archive-date=7 February 2021|access-date=7 February 2021|website=NME}}</ref> Lipa went on to host the festival for the second year in 2019, with [[Miley Cyrus]] included as part of the performer line-up.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Seemayer|first=Zach|date=9 September 2019|title=Dua Lipa on Why It Was So Special to Have Miley Cyrus Perform at Her Sunny Hill Festival in Kosovo (Exclusive)|url=https://www.etonline.com/dua-lipa-on-why-it-was-so-special-to-have-miley-cyrus-perform-at-her-sunny-hill-festival-in-kosovo|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190911175458/https://www.etonline.com/dua-lipa-on-why-it-was-so-special-to-have-miley-cyrus-perform-at-her-sunny-hill-festival-in-kosovo|archive-date=11 September 2019|access-date=6 April 2020|work=Entertainment Tonight}}</ref> In mid-November 2018, Lipa was part of a campaign organised by [[UNICEF]] called "Go Blue" in support of children's rights, on the occasion of [[Children's Day|World Children's Day]] (20 November).<ref>{{Cite web|last=Ferguson|first=Sarah|date=19 November 2018|title=Go Blue For UNICEF On World Children's Day|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/unicefusa/2018/11/19/go-blue-for-unicef-on-world-childrens-day/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181119190027/https://www.forbes.com/sites/unicefusa/2018/11/19/go-blue-for-unicef-on-world-childrens-day/|archive-date=19 November 2018|access-date=27 July 2020|website=[[Forbes]]}}</ref> Her contribution consisted of a short video about dressing in blue or displaying the colour blue, with her in a studio re-recording the lyrics of her song "Be the One" (2015). She changed the word "red" to "blue" in the song for the occasion.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Maxourls|first=Christina|date=21 November 2018|title='Stranger Things' star Millie Bobby Brown is now UNICEF's youngest-ever Goodwill Ambassador|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2018/11/21/entertainment/millie-bobby-brown-unicef-trnd/index.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181122021719/https://edition.cnn.com/2018/11/21/entertainment/millie-bobby-brown-unicef-trnd/index.html|archive-date=22 November 2018|access-date=27 July 2020|work=[[CNN]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=14 November 2018|title=Millie Bobby 'Blue' leads cast of stars in new UNICEF video for World Children's Day|url=https://www.unicef.org/press-releases/millie-bobby-blue-leads-cast-stars-new-unicef-video-world-childrens-day|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200611191425/https://www.unicef.org/press-releases/millie-bobby-blue-leads-cast-stars-new-unicef-video-world-childrens-day|archive-date=11 June 2020|access-date=7 February 2021|website=UNICEF}}</ref> In December 2018, Lipa participated in a benefit concert for the [[Ellie Goulding]]'s "Streets of London" annual charity event at [[Wembley Arena]], which "funds specialist support for people who are homeless in London and raises awareness about homelessness."<ref>{{Cite web|last=Moore|first=Sam|date=13 November 2018|title=Ellie Goulding, Dua Lipa, Bastille and more confirmed for huge Wembley homeless charity gig|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/ellie-goulding-dua-lipa-bastille-streets-of-london-charity-gig-sse-wembley-arena-december-2402056|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181114014103/https://www.nme.com/news/music/ellie-goulding-dua-lipa-bastille-streets-of-london-charity-gig-sse-wembley-arena-december-2402056|archive-date=14 November 2018|access-date=6 February 2021|website=NME}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Smyth|first=David|date=21 December 2018|title=Ellie Goulding review: Dua Lipa, Bastille and more out in force for hit-heavy Streets of London charity gig|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/culture/music/ellie-goulding-review-dua-lipa-bastille-and-more-out-in-force-for-hit-heavy-streets-of-london-charity-gig-a4023541.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206064501/https://www.standard.co.uk/culture/music/ellie-goulding-review-dua-lipa-bastille-and-more-out-in-force-for-hit-heavy-streets-of-london-charity-gig-a4023541.html|archive-date=6 February 2021|access-date=6 February 2021|website=Evening Standard}}</ref> In April 2019, she became an UNICEF supporter during a three-day visit to a camp for refugee children and youth in [[Beirut]], Lebanon.<ref>{{Cite web|date=15 April 2019|title=Recording artist Dua Lipa visits Lebanon with UNICEF to meet refugee children and young people|url=https://www.unicef.org/press-releases/recording-artist-dua-lipa-visits-lebanon-unicef-meet-refugee-children-and-young|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416052453/https://www.unicef.org/press-releases/recording-artist-dua-lipa-visits-lebanon-unicef-meet-refugee-children-and-young|archive-date=16 April 2019|access-date=1 March 2021|website=UNICEF}}</ref> The camp included many uprooted by the [[Syrian civil war|conflict in Syria]] who did not have "adequate" health care or education and Lipa also visited young [[Palestinians]] and [[Syrians]] in [[Bourj el-Barajneh#Refugee camp|Bourj el-Barajneh refugee camp]].<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Aniftos|first=Rania|date=16 April 2019|title=Dua Lipa Meets Refugees in Lebanon with UNICEF|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8507512/dua-lipa-meets-refugees-in-lebanon-with-unicef|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190417033251/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8507512/dua-lipa-meets-refugees-in-lebanon-with-unicef|archive-date=17 April 2019|access-date=2 May 2020|magazine=Billboard}}</ref> She subsequently supported a campaign by her management company with a plan to raise £100,000 to help raise awareness of charities such as [[SANE (charity)#Black Dog campaign|The Black Dog]] and [[Campaign Against Living Miserably|CALM]].<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Aniftos|first=Rania|date=3 October 2019|title=Dua Lipa Supports TaP Music's Call to Action for Mental Health Awareness in Creative Industries|url=https://assets.billboard.com/articles/news/8532125/dua-lipa-tap-music-call-to-action-mental-health-awareness|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206162404/https://assets.billboard.com/articles/news/8532125/dua-lipa-tap-music-call-to-action-mental-health-awareness|archive-date=6 February 2021|access-date=6 February 2021|magazine=Billboard}}</ref>

She asked for a better mental health care for artists in creative industries, as she was "shocked" to read that "suicide rates amongst women working in the arts are almost 70% higher than in the world population". Lipa described mental health as the "issue of our generation".<ref>{{Cite web|last=Aubrey|first=Elizabeth|date=4 October 2019|title=Dua Lipa calls for better mental health care in the creative industries|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-calls-better-mental-health-creative-industries-2553989|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191005234926/https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-calls-better-mental-health-creative-industries-2553989|archive-date=5 October 2019|access-date=6 February 2021|website=NME}}</ref> On 26 November 2019, following the [[2019 Albania earthquake]], Lipa asked fans for donations and support for victims.<ref name="DeutscheWellealb">{{cite news|date=30 November 2019|title=Albania quake toll hits 51 as search for survivors ends|publisher=[[Deutsche Welle]]|url=https://www.dw.com/en/albania-quake-toll-hits-51-as-search-for-survivors-ends/a-51483420|url-status=live|access-date=30 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191130212002/https://www.dw.com/en/albania-quake-toll-hits-51-as-search-for-survivors-ends/a-51483420|archive-date=30 November 2019}}</ref><ref name="AlJazeerapop">{{cite news|date=29 November 2019|title=Pop stars rally for Albania following deadly earthquake|publisher=[[Al Jazeera English|Al Jazeera]]|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/11/pop-stars-rally-albania-deadly-earthquake-191129065925319.html|url-status=live|access-date=30 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191129101207/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/11/pop-stars-rally-albania-deadly-earthquake-191129065925319.html|archive-date=29 November 2019}}</ref> To raise funds she co-released a limited edition line of t-shirts called "Pray for Albania" in collaboration with Albanian fashion designers. All of the proceeds went to families and victims affected by the seismic event.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Muñoz|first=Sandra|date=4 December 2019|title=Dua Lipa diseña una camiseta para ayudar a las víctimas del terremoto de Albania|url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/es/moda/compras/a30116607/dua-lipa-camiseta-benefica-terremoto-albania/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200611162827/https://www.harpersbazaar.com/es/moda/compras/a30116607/dua-lipa-camiseta-benefica-terremoto-albania/|archive-date=11 June 2020|access-date=2 May 2020|website=|publisher=Harper's Bazaar|language=es}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=4 December 2019|title=Pray for Albania Tee|url=https://store.dualipa.com/products/pray-for-albania-t-shirt|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200104131118/https://store.dualipa.com/products/pray-for-albania-t-shirt|archive-date=4 January 2020|access-date=7 February 2021|website=Dua Lipa Store}}</ref> On 15 March 2020, she asked her fans to make donations to the [[United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees|UNHCR]] agency to deal with COVID-19 pandemic because refugees are "the most vulnerable on this planet" and they "often live in crowded places" with "limited health services".<ref>{{Cite web|last=Subair|first=Eni|date=4 May 2020|title=Dua Lipa shares 6 tips on looking after your mental health|url=https://www.vogue.in/wellness/content/dua-lipa-shares-tips-on-how-to-look-after-your-mental-health|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200509081437/https://www.vogue.in/wellness/content/dua-lipa-shares-tips-on-how-to-look-after-your-mental-health|archive-date=9 May 2020|access-date=9 February 2021|website=[[Vogue India]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=15 March 2020|title=Dua Lipa urges fans to donate for coronavirus crisis|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/english/music/news/dua-lipa-urges-fans-to-donate-for-coronavirus-crisis/articleshow/74643884.cms|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323082919/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/english/music/news/dua-lipa-urges-fans-to-donate-for-coronavirus-crisis/articleshow/74643884.cms|archive-date=23 March 2020|access-date=9 February 2021|website=[[The Times of India]]}}</ref> In the same month, she was part of a television special called "Home Fest" on ''[[The Late Late Show with James Corden]] From His Garage'' with the goal of raising money for [[Centers for Disease Control and Prevention|CDC]] and [[Feed the Children]] where she performed her song, "Don't Start Now" (2019), from an apartment in London.<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Zemler|first=Emily|date=31 March 2020|title=Watch BTS, Dua Lipa, Billie Eilish Perform on Special Edition of 'Corden'|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/bts-dua-lipa-home-fest-corden-975614/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200401122452/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/bts-dua-lipa-home-fest-corden-975614/|archive-date=1 April 2020|access-date=6 February 2021|magazine=Rolling Stone}}</ref> On 16 May 2020, she did a live performance of her song "[[Break My Heart (Dua Lipa song)|Break My Heart]]" (2020) on the television special ''[[Graduate Together: America Honors the High School Class of 2020]]'' aimed at the high school students whose graduation ceremonies and [[prom]]s were cancelled due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Daw|first=Stephen|date=16 May 2020|title=Barack Obama, Jonas Brothers & Karol G and More: 5 Key Moments From 'Graduate Together'|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/9379297/barack-obama-jonas-brothers-karol-g-graduate-together-highlights|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200518004135/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/9379297/barack-obama-jonas-brothers-karol-g-graduate-together-highlights|archive-date=18 May 2020|access-date=27 July 2020|magazine=Billboard}}</ref> At the end of May 2020, she participated in a digital event called "Dream with Us" with the aim of raising funds,<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Mamo|first=Heran|date=28 May 2020|title=Dua Lipa, Jason Derulo, Becky G, Maluma & More Stars Join OneHuManity's 'Dream With Us' 24-Hour Livestream|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9392727/onehumanity-dream-with-us-24-hour-livestream|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200611213349/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9392727/onehumanity-dream-with-us-24-hour-livestream|archive-date=11 June 2020|access-date=1 March 2021|magazine=Billboard}}</ref> whose event consisted of a streaming concert at which a portion of proceeds would go to organizations which help fight [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Darmon|first=Aynslee|date=29 May 2020|title=Avril Lavigne, Dua Lipa And More Join OHM Live's 24 Hour Livestream|url=https://etcanada.com/news/650610/avril-lavigne-dua-lipa-and-more-join-ohm-lives-24-hour-livestream/|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200612120247/https://etcanada.com/news/650610/avril-lavigne-dua-lipa-and-more-join-ohm-lives-24-hour-livestream/|archive-date=12 June 2020|access-date=4 March 2021|website=Entertainment Tonight}}</ref>

She took part in a charitable project operated by [[BBC Radio 1]] for a cover version of "[[Times Like These (song)#Live Lounge Allstars charity single|Times Like These]]" released on 23 April 2020 for the [[Live Lounge]] segment.<ref>{{Cite web|date=20 April 2020|title=BBC Radio 1 to record biggest ever Live Lounge for charity amid Coronavirus crisis, featuring Dua Lipa, Chris Martin of Coldplay, AJ Tracey, Rita Ora, Ellie Goulding, YUNGBLUD and more|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2020/live-lounge|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200611131944/https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2020/live-lounge|archive-date=11 June 2020|access-date=23 April 2020|work=[[BBC]]}}</ref> She was part of the [[charity supergroup]] Live Lounge Allstars in which each member recorded and filmed their contribution to the song from their respective households to encourage social distancing in which profits from the single would primarily go to ''[[Children in Need]]'' and [[Comic Relief]], as well as [[COVID-19 Solidarity Response Fund]].<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Rowley|first=Glen|date=20 April 2020|title=Dua Lipa, Chris Martin to Cover Foo Fighters' 'Times Like These' for Charity|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9361774/dua-lipa-chris-martin-foo-fighters-times-like-these-cover-for-charity|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200420230120/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9361774/dua-lipa-chris-martin-foo-fighters-times-like-these-cover-for-charity|archive-date=20 April 2020|access-date=4 March 2021|magazine=Billboard}}</ref> She used social media to encourage Lebanese citizens to [[Blood donation|donate blood]] to victims affected by the [[2020 Beirut explosion]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Lewis|first=Isobel|date=5 August 2020|title=Beirut explosion: Dua Lipa and Priyanka Chopra lead celebrity reactions to 'devastating' incident|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/beirut-explosion-dua-lipa-priyanka-chopra-donate-blood-lebanon-a9654596.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200809003831/https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/beirut-explosion-dua-lipa-priyanka-chopra-donate-blood-lebanon-a9654596.html|archive-date=9 August 2020|access-date=7 February 2021|website=The Independent}}</ref> She donated 5,000 euros to the Theatre of Dodona so that the venue could have its own ticket system and website.<ref>{{Cite web|date=7 August 2020|title=Dua Lipa i bëri dhuratë teatrit 'Dodona'|trans-title=Dua Lipa gave a gift to the theater 'Dodona'|url=https://rtv21.tv/dua-lipa-i-beri-dhurate-teatrit-dodona/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201202154356/https://rtv21.tv/dua-lipa-i-beri-dhurate-teatrit-dodona/|archive-date=2 December 2020|access-date=12 February 2021|website=[[RTV21]]|language=Albanian}}</ref> She was part of an initiative organized by Belgian singer Angèle and KickCancer Foundation to fund research against childhood cancer, and it was about a charity raffle in which Lipa offered a manuscript of her song "Don't Start Now" (2019) as a prize.<ref>{{Cite web|date=15 February 2021|title=Angèle organise une tombola pour financer la recherche contre le cancer de l'enfant|url=https://www.bfmtv.com/people/angele-organise-une-tombola-pour-financer-la-recherche-contre-le-cancer-de-l-enfant_AN-202102150125.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210215085412/https://www.bfmtv.com/people/angele-organise-une-tombola-pour-financer-la-recherche-contre-le-cancer-de-l-enfant_AN-202102150125.html|archive-date=15 February 2021|access-date=15 February 2021|publisher=[[BFM TV]]|language=French}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Win Dua Lipa's manuscript of her number 1 hit 'Don't Start Now' !|url=https://www.naojo.com/en/experiences/gagnez-le-manuscrit-du-hit-dont-start-de-dua-lipa/rules|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210214175338/https://www.naojo.com/en/experiences/gagnez-le-manuscrit-du-hit-dont-start-de-dua-lipa/rules|archive-date=14 February 2021|access-date=15 February 2021|website=Naojo}}</ref> She performed at 2021 [[Elton John AIDS Foundation Academy Award Party]] virtually to benefit the [[Elton John AIDS Foundation|AIDS Foundation]] to combat [[HIV/AIDS|HIV disease]], whose event raised US$3&nbsp;million.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Hume|first=Ashley|title=Lady Gaga, Dua Lipa and Dr. Fauci Among Guests at Elton John's Virtual Oscar Party|url=https://variety.com/2021/scene/news/lady-gaga-dua-lipa-elton-john-oscar-party-1234960646/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210426201914/https://variety.com/2021/scene/news/lady-gaga-dua-lipa-elton-john-oscar-party-1234960646/|archive-date=26 April 2021|access-date=26 April 2021|website=Variety|date=26 April 2021}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Lipa's first name "Dua" was her grandmother's suggestion and means "love" in [[Albanian language|Albanian]].<ref name="fun" /> She is occasionally referred to affectionately by fans as "Dula Peep", which originated as a [[mispronunciation]] by American talk show host [[Wendy Williams]] in 2018.<ref name="Wendy Dula Peep">{{cite news |last1=Syd |first1=Robinson |title=Wendy Williams Just Tried To Say Dua Lipa's Name And It's Everything |url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/sydrobinson1/wendy-williams-just-mispronounced-dua-lipas-name |access-date=27 November 2021 |work=Buzzfeed |date=23 May 2018 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20230120111443/https://www.buzzfeed.com/sydrobinson1/wendy-williams-just-mispronounced-dua-lipas-name |archive-date=20 January 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> Since then, she has positively embraced the nickname.<ref name="Dula Peep Fallon">{{cite news |last1=Wang |first1=Steffanee |title=Dua Lipa Is Cool with You Calling Her 'Dula Peep' |url=https://www.nylon.com/dua-lipa-dula-peep |access-date=27 November 2021 |work=Nylon |date=19 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211008013608/https://www.nylon.com/dua-lipa-dula-peep |archive-date=8 October 2021 |url-status=live}}</ref>

Lipa's native language is Albanian.<ref name="talecities"/> She was born and grew up mostly in [[London]], and has a [[Estuary English|London accent]] when speaking English.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Walsh|first=Lara|date=10 February 2019|title=These Tweets About Dua Lipa's Accent at the 2019 Grammys Will Make You Laugh Out Loud|url=https://www.elitedaily.com/p/these-tweets-about-dua-lipas-accent-at-the-2019-grammys-will-make-you-laugh-out-loud-15940053|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190211041040/https://www.elitedaily.com/p/these-tweets-about-dua-lipas-accent-at-the-2019-grammys-will-make-you-laugh-out-loud-15940053|archive-date=11 February 2019|access-date=19 January 2021|website=[[Elite Daily]]}}</ref> Despite this, she can speak her native language fluently and described her "dual identity" as her "strength".<ref>{{Cite web |date=29 September 2022 |title=Dua Lipa: I speak English and Albanian, dual identity is my strength. When I was a child I was ashamed of my name... |url=https://www.voxnews.al/english/lifestyle/dua-lipa-flas-anglisht-dhe-shqip-identiteti-i-dyfishte-eshte-forca-ime-i20803 |access-date=14 May 2024 |website=Vox News}}</ref>

Lipa has described herself as an "honorary [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] supporter", after her song "One Kiss" was adopted by the football club's fans in the wake of her performance at the 2018 UEFA Champions League final, since becoming a Reds anthem after significant Liverpool victories.<ref>{{cite web |title=Why do Liverpool fans sing Dua Lipa's song 'One Kiss'? Lyrics, video & how chart hit became an Anfield anthem |url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/why-liverpool-fans-sing-dua-lipa-song-one-kiss-lyrics-video/blt131ebf5204af8e3f |website=[[Goal.com]] |access-date=29 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220313064228/https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/why-liverpool-fans-sing-dua-lipa-song-one-kiss-lyrics-video/blt131ebf5204af8e3f |archive-date=13 March 2022 |url-status=dead |last=Khairi |first=Nick |date=10 March 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title='One Kiss is motivation to celebrate more' – How Liverpool embraced their new anthem |url=https://www.thisisanfield.com/2022/07/one-kiss-is-motivation-to-celebrate-more-how-liverpool-embraced-their-new-anthem/ |website=This is Anfield |date=15 July 2022 |access-date=29 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220715100815/https://www.thisisanfield.com/2022/07/one-kiss-is-motivation-to-celebrate-more-how-liverpool-embraced-their-new-anthem/ |archive-date=15 July 2022 |url-status=live |last=Sear |first=Jack}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Why do Liverpool fans sing 'One Kiss' by Dua Lipa? The story behind the new anthem for Jurgen Klopp's men |url=https://www.sportingnews.com/uk/soccer/news/liverpool-fans-one-kiss-dua-lipa/kbe3fcdmtvvnptvn7ufejdyh |website=[[Sporting News]] |date=28 May 2022 |access-date=29 November 2022 |last=Farrell |first=Dom |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220623091832/https://www.sportingnews.com/uk/soccer/news/liverpool-fans-one-kiss-dua-lipa/kbe3fcdmtvvnptvn7ufejdyh |archive-date=23 June 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 27 November 2022, Lipa was granted Albanian citizenship by [[President of Albania|president]] [[Bajram Begaj]], one day before the country's 110th independence celebrations.<ref name="Dua Lipa granted Albanian citizenship by president in Tirana">{{Cite web |date=27 November 2022 |title=Dua Lipa granted Albanian citizenship by president in Tirana |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2022/nov/27/dua-lipa-granted-albanian-citizenship-by-president-in-tirana |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221127192326/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2022/nov/27/dua-lipa-granted-albanian-citizenship-by-president-in-tirana |archive-date=27 November 2022 |access-date=25 January 2023 |website=[[The Guardian]]}}</ref><ref name="AlbanianCitizenship">{{Cite web |date=27 November 2022 |title=Presidenti i Republikës Sh. T. Z. Bajram Begaj i dorëzon dekretin e shtetësisë shqiptare këngëtares së famshme Dua Lipa |url=https://president.al/presidenti-republikes-sh-t-z-bajram-begaj-dorezon-dekretin-e-shtetesise-shqiptare-kengetares-se-famshme-dua-lipa/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221127152510/https://president.al/presidenti-republikes-sh-t-z-bajram-begaj-dorezon-dekretin-e-shtetesise-shqiptare-kengetares-se-famshme-dua-lipa/ |archive-date=27 November 2022 |access-date=27 November 2022 |website=Presidenti i Republikës së Shqipërisë |language=sq-AL |url-status=live}}</ref>

From June 2019 to December 2021, Lipa was in a relationship with model Anwar Hadid.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Dua Lipa's Dating History: From Anwar Hadid to Callum Turner |url=https://people.com/all-about-dua-lipa-dating-history-7502520 |access-date=2024-05-05 |website=Peoplemag |language=en}}</ref> Since January 2024, Lipa has been dating actor [[Callum Turner]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |date=2024-04-26 |title=Dua Lipa and Callum Turner Have a Stylish Date Night at a Gala |url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/celebrity/latest/a46429054/dua-lipa-callum-turner-relationship-timeline/ |access-date=2024-05-05 |magazine=Harper's BAZAAR |language=en-US}}</ref>

